41static lstr_t t_enum_get_prefix(const iopc_enum_t *en)
42{
43 lstr_t ns = LSTR_NULL;
44
45 if (t_iopc_attr_check_prefix(&en->attrs, &ns) < 0) {
46 ns = t_camelcase_to_c(LSTR(en->name));
47 }
48 lstr_ascii_toupper(&ns);
49 return ns;
50}

52/** Give the extra length for the encoding of an IOP tag. */
53static inline int iopc_tag_len(int32_t tag)
54{
55 /* Tags 0..29 are encoded inline -> 0 byte,
56 * Tags 30..255 are encoded as value 30 plus 1 byte,
57 * Tags 256..65535 are encoded as value 31 plus 2 extra bytes */
58 return (tag >= 30) + (tag >= 256);
59}

66static iopc_field_t *iopc_bubble_field(qv_t(iopc_field) *fields, int pos,
67 size_t size)
68{
69 int lost = INT_MAX, match = 0;
70 iopc_field_t **tab = fields->tab + pos;
71
72 for (int i = 0; i < fields->len - pos; i++) {
73 iopc_field_t *f = tab[i];
74 int f_lost = ROUND_UP(size, f->align) - size;
75
76 if (f_lost < lost) {
77 lost = f_lost;
78 match = i;
79 }
80 }
81
82 if (match) {
83 iopc_field_t *f = tab[match];
84
85 p_move(tab + 1, tab, match);
86 tab[0] = f;
87 }
88 return tab[0];
89}

91/* TODO Do it systematically somewhere else. */
92static void iopc_struct_build_fields_by_tag(iopc_struct_t *st)
93{
94 if (st->fields_by_tag.len == st->fields.len) {
95 return;
96 }
97
98 qv_extend_tab(&st->fields_by_tag, &st->fields);
99 qv_sort(iopc_field)(&st->fields_by_tag, ^int (iopc_field_t * const *f1,
100 iopc_field_t * const *f2) {
101 return (*f1)->tag - (*f2)->tag;
102 });
103}

105/** Calculate sizes and alignments then and optimize the fields order to
106 * minimize the structure size.
107 */
108static void iopc_struct_optimize(iopc_struct_t *st)
109{
110 size_t size = 0;
111 size_t opt_size = 0;
112 size_t orig_size = 0;
113 bool do_reorder;
114
115 if (st->size || st->optimized) {
116 return;
117 }
118
119 if (st->type == STRUCT_TYPE_UNION) {
120 /* iop_tag field */
121 st->align = alignof(uint16_t);
122 } else
123 if (st->type == STRUCT_TYPE_CLASS) {
124 /* __vptr field */
125 st->align = alignof(void *);
126 } else {
127 st->align = 1;
128 }
129 tab_for_each_entry(f, &st->fields) {
130 iopc_field_compute_size(f);
131 st->align = MAX(st->align, f->align);
132 orig_size = ROUND_UP(orig_size, f->align) + f->size;
133 opt_size += f->size;
134 }
135 orig_size = ROUND_UP(orig_size, st->align);
136
137 iopc_struct_build_fields_by_tag(st);
138 qv_extend_tab(&st->fields_in_c_struct_order, &st->fields_by_tag);
139
140 if (st->type == STRUCT_TYPE_UNION) {
141 /*
142 * union is struct { uint16_t tag; union { ... }; }
143 *
144 * so its align is at least 2, and its size is an alignment + max size
145 * of any member of the union.
146 */
147 tab_for_each_entry(f, &st->fields) {
148 size = MAX(size, f->size);
149 }
150 size = ROUND_UP(size, st->align);
151 st->size = st->align + size;
152 return;
153 }
154
155 if (iopc_is_class(st->type) || iopc_is_snmp_st(st->type)) {
156 /* XXX: we don't want to reorder class/snmpObj fields to ease
157 * debugging and backward compatibility. */
158 do_reorder = false;
159 } else {
160 do_reorder = iopc_attr_check(&st->attrs, IOPC_ATTR_NO_REORDER,
161 NULL) < 0;
162 }
163
164 for (int i = 0; i < st->fields_in_c_struct_order.len; i++) {
165 iopc_field_t *f;
166
167 if (do_reorder) {
168 f = iopc_bubble_field(&st->fields_in_c_struct_order, i, size);
169 } else {
170 f = st->fields_in_c_struct_order.tab[i];
171 }
172
173 size = ROUND_UP(size, f->align) + f->size;
174 }
175 st->size = size = ROUND_UP(size, st->align);
176
177 if (do_reorder && st->size - opt_size >= st->align)
178 warn_loc("suboptimal type size (%s packed is %zd, size is %d@%d)",
179 st->loc, st->name, opt_size, st->size, st->align);
180#if 0
181 if (orig_size > size) {
182 warn_loc("%s:\torig:%3zd now:%3zd gain:%2zd packed:%3zd",
183 st->loc, st->name, orig_size, size,
184 orig_size - size, opt_size);
185 }
186#else
187 IGNORE(orig_size);
188#endif
189
190 st->optimized = true;
191}

196/** Same as \ref iop_scalar_type_get_size_and_alignment but for optional
197 * types. */
198static void iop_opt_type_get_size_and_alignment(iop_type_t type,
199 uint16_t *nullable size,
200 uint8_t *nullable align)
201{
202 static struct {
203 uint16_t size;
204 uint8_t align;
205 } sizes_and_alignments[] = {
206#define SIZE_ALIGN(type_t) { sizeof(type_t), alignof(type_t) }
207
208 [IOP_T_VOID] = SIZE_ALIGN(bool),
209 [IOP_T_BOOL] = SIZE_ALIGN(opt_bool_t),
210 [IOP_T_U8] = SIZE_ALIGN(opt_u8_t),
211 [IOP_T_I8] = SIZE_ALIGN(opt_i8_t),
212 [IOP_T_U16] = SIZE_ALIGN(opt_u16_t),
213 [IOP_T_I16] = SIZE_ALIGN(opt_i16_t),
214 [IOP_T_U32] = SIZE_ALIGN(opt_u32_t),
215 [IOP_T_I32] = SIZE_ALIGN(opt_i32_t),
216 [IOP_T_ENUM] = SIZE_ALIGN(opt_i32_t),
217 [IOP_T_U64] = SIZE_ALIGN(opt_u64_t),
218 [IOP_T_I64] = SIZE_ALIGN(opt_i64_t),
219 [IOP_T_DOUBLE] = SIZE_ALIGN(opt_double_t),
220 [IOP_T_STRING] = SIZE_ALIGN(lstr_t),
221 [IOP_T_DATA] = SIZE_ALIGN(lstr_t),
222 [IOP_T_XML] = SIZE_ALIGN(lstr_t),
223 [IOP_T_UNION] = SIZE_ALIGN(void *),
224 [IOP_T_STRUCT] = SIZE_ALIGN(void *),
225
226#undef SIZE_ALIGN
227 };
228
229 typeof(sizes_and_alignments[0]) res;
230
231 res = sizes_and_alignments[type];
232 if (size) {
233 *size = res.size;
234 }
235 if (align) {
236 *align = res.align;
237 }
238}

240/** Get the field size and alignment for the C type associated to an IOP
241 * scalar type.
242 */
243static void iop_scalar_type_get_size_and_alignment(iop_type_t type,
244 uint16_t *nullable size,
245 uint8_t *nullable align)
246{
247 static struct {
248 uint16_t size;
249 uint8_t align;
250 } sizes_and_alignments[] = {
251#define SIZE_ALIGN(type_t) { sizeof(type_t), alignof(type_t) }
252
253 [IOP_T_VOID] = { 0, alignof(bool) },
254 [IOP_T_BOOL] = SIZE_ALIGN(bool),
255 [IOP_T_U8] = SIZE_ALIGN(uint8_t),
256 [IOP_T_I8] = SIZE_ALIGN(int8_t),
257 [IOP_T_U16] = SIZE_ALIGN(uint16_t),
258 [IOP_T_I16] = SIZE_ALIGN(int16_t),
259 [IOP_T_U32] = SIZE_ALIGN(uint32_t),
260 [IOP_T_I32] = SIZE_ALIGN(int32_t),
261 [IOP_T_ENUM] = SIZE_ALIGN(int32_t),
262 [IOP_T_U64] = SIZE_ALIGN(uint64_t),
263 [IOP_T_I64] = SIZE_ALIGN(int64_t),
264 [IOP_T_DOUBLE] = SIZE_ALIGN(double),
265 [IOP_T_STRING] = SIZE_ALIGN(lstr_t),
266 [IOP_T_DATA] = SIZE_ALIGN(lstr_t),
267 [IOP_T_XML] = SIZE_ALIGN(lstr_t),
268
269#undef SIZE_ALIGN
270 };
271 typeof(sizes_and_alignments[0]) res;
272
273 if (!iop_type_is_scalar(type)) {
274 e_panic("should not happen");
275 }
276
277 res = sizes_and_alignments[type];
278 if (size) {
279 *size = res.size;
280 }
281 if (align) {
282 *align = res.align;
283 }
284}

286static uint8_t iop_struct_get_align(const iop_struct_t *st);
287
288/* XXX The logic is the same (and *should* stay the same) as for
289 * "iopc_field_compute_size" except that the description type is different. */
290static uint16_t iop_field_get_align(const iop_field_t *f)
291{
292 uint8_t align;
293 uint16_t flags = f->flags;
294
295 if (TST_BIT(&flags, IOP_FIELD_IS_REFERENCE)) {
296 align = alignof(void *);
297 } else
298 if (f->repeat == IOP_R_OPTIONAL) {
299 iop_opt_type_get_size_and_alignment(f->type, NULL, &align);
300 } else
301 if (f->repeat == IOP_R_REPEATED) {
302 align = alignof(IOP_ARRAY_OF(void));
303 } else
304 if (iop_type_is_scalar(f->type)) {
305 iop_scalar_type_get_size_and_alignment(f->type, NULL, &align);
306 } else
307 if (iop_field_is_class(f)) {
308 align = alignof(void *);
309 } else {
310 align = iop_struct_get_align(f->u1.st_desc);
311 }
312
313 return align;
314}
315
316/* TODO We may want to expose it someday and also to extend iop_struct_t to
317 * have the alignment in it. */
318/* XXX The there is no caching of structs alignments (and we might want to add
319 * some at some point. The calculation is in O(N) where N is the number of
320 * inlined fields and subfields in the struct/union, which is not so bad. */
321static uint8_t iop_struct_get_align(const iop_struct_t *st)
322{
323 uint8_t align = 1;
324
325 for (int i = 0; i < st->fields_len; i++) {
326 const iop_field_t *f = &st->fields[i];
327
328 align = MAX(align, iop_field_get_align(f));
329 }
330
331 return align;
332}
333
334static void iopc_field_compute_size(iopc_field_t *f)
335{
336 if (f->size) {
337 return;
338 }
339
340 if (f->is_ref) {
341 f->align = alignof(void *);
342 f->size = sizeof(void *);
343 } else
344 if (f->repeat == IOP_R_OPTIONAL) {
345 iop_opt_type_get_size_and_alignment(f->kind, &f->size, &f->align);
346 } else
347 if (f->repeat == IOP_R_REPEATED) {
348 f->align = alignof(IOP_ARRAY_OF(void));
349 f->size = sizeof(IOP_ARRAY_OF(void));
350 } else
351 if (iop_type_is_scalar(f->kind)) {
352 iop_scalar_type_get_size_and_alignment(f->kind, &f->size, &f->align);
353 } else
354 if (iopc_field_type_is_class(f)) {
355 f->align = alignof(void *);
356 f->size = sizeof(void *);
357 } else
358 if (f->has_external_type) {
359 f->align = iop_struct_get_align(f->external_st);
360 f->size = f->external_st->size;
361 } else {
362 iopc_struct_optimize(f->struct_def);
363 f->align = f->struct_def->align;
364 f->size = f->struct_def->size;
365 }
366}

371static void pp_field_with_type(sb_t *sb, const iopc_field_t *f, int indent)
372{
373 t_scope;
374 const char *type = NULL;
375 const char *old_type = NULL;
376 bool type_is_class = false;
377
378 if (f->kind == IOP_T_STRUCT && f->struct_def->type == STRUCT_TYPE_CLASS) {
379 type_is_class = true;
380 }
381
382 switch (f->repeat) {
383 case IOP_R_REPEATED:
384 switch (f->kind) {
385 case IOP_T_U8:
386 type = "iop_array_u8_t ";
387 old_type = "IOP_ARRAY_OF(uint8_t) ";
388 break;
389 case IOP_T_I8:
390 type = "iop_array_i8_t ";
391 old_type = "IOP_ARRAY_OF(int8_t) ";
392 break;
393 case IOP_T_U16:
394 type = "iop_array_u16_t ";
395 old_type = "IOP_ARRAY_OF(uint16_t) ";
396 break;
397 case IOP_T_I16:
398 type = "iop_array_i16_t ";
399 old_type = "IOP_ARRAY_OF(int16_t) ";
400 break;
401 case IOP_T_U32:
402 type = "iop_array_u32_t ";
403 old_type = "IOP_ARRAY_OF(uint32_t) ";
404 break;
405 case IOP_T_I32:
406 type = "iop_array_i32_t ";
407 old_type = "IOP_ARRAY_OF(int32_t) ";
408 break;
409 case IOP_T_U64:
410 type = "iop_array_u64_t ";
411 old_type = "IOP_ARRAY_OF(uint64_t) ";
412 break;
413 case IOP_T_I64:
414 type = "iop_array_i64_t ";
415 old_type = "IOP_ARRAY_OF(int64_t) ";
416 break;
417 case IOP_T_BOOL:
418 type = "iop_array_bool_t ";
419 old_type = "IOP_ARRAY_OF(bool) ";
420 break;
421 case IOP_T_DOUBLE:
422 type = "iop_array_double_t ";
423 old_type = "IOP_ARRAY_OF(double) ";
424 break;
425 case IOP_T_STRING:
426 case IOP_T_XML:
427 type = "iop_array_lstr_t ";
428 old_type = "IOP_ARRAY_OF(lstr_t) ";
429 break;
430 case IOP_T_DATA:
431 type = "iop_array_lstr_t ";
432 old_type = "IOP_ARRAY_OF(iop_data_t) ";
433 break;
434 case IOP_T_VOID:
435 /* Repeated void are forbidden in the parser. */
436 assert (false);
437 break;
438 default:
439 sb_addnc(sb, indent, ' ');
440 sb_addf(sb, "%s__%s__array_t %s;\n",
441 t_iopc_path_to_c(f->type_path),
442 t_iopc_name_to_c(f->type_name),
443 t_iopc_name_to_c(f->name));
444 return;
445 }
446 break;
447
448 case IOP_R_OPTIONAL:
449 switch (f->kind) {
450 case IOP_T_U8: type = "opt_u8_t "; break;
451 case IOP_T_I8: type = "opt_i8_t "; break;
452 case IOP_T_U16: type = "opt_u16_t "; break;
453 case IOP_T_I16: type = "opt_i16_t "; break;
454 case IOP_T_U32: type = "opt_u32_t "; break;
455 case IOP_T_I32: type = "opt_i32_t "; break;
456 case IOP_T_U64: type = "opt_u64_t "; break;
457 case IOP_T_I64: type = "opt_i64_t "; break;
458 case IOP_T_BOOL: type = "opt_bool_t "; break;
459 case IOP_T_VOID: type = "bool "; break;
460 case IOP_T_DOUBLE: type = "opt_double_t "; break;
461 case IOP_T_STRING: type = "lstr_t "; break;
462 case IOP_T_XML: type = "lstr_t "; break;
463 case IOP_T_DATA: type = "lstr_t "; break;
464 case IOP_T_ENUM:
465 sb_addnc(sb, indent, ' ');
466 sb_addf(sb, "%s__%s__opt_t %s;\n",
467 t_iopc_path_to_c(f->type_path),
468 t_iopc_name_to_c(f->type_name),
469 t_iopc_name_to_c(f->name));
470 return;
471 default:
472 sb_addnc(sb, indent, ' ');
473 sb_addf(sb, "struct %s__%s__t *nullable %s;\n",
474 t_iopc_path_to_c(f->type_path),
475 t_iopc_name_to_c(f->type_name),
476 t_iopc_name_to_c(f->name));
477 return;
478 }
479 break;
480
481 default:
482 switch (f->kind) {
483 case IOP_T_U8: type = "uint8_t "; break;
484 case IOP_T_I8: type = "int8_t "; break;
485 case IOP_T_U16: type = "uint16_t "; break;
486 case IOP_T_I16: type = "int16_t "; break;
487 case IOP_T_U32: type = "uint32_t "; break;
488 case IOP_T_I32: type = "int32_t "; break;
489 case IOP_T_U64: type = "uint64_t "; break;
490 case IOP_T_I64: type = "int64_t "; break;
491 case IOP_T_BOOL: type = "bool "; break;
492 case IOP_T_VOID:
493 /* void type is not present in struct or union */
494 return;
495 case IOP_T_DOUBLE: type = "double "; break;
496 case IOP_T_STRING: type = "lstr_t "; break;
497 case IOP_T_DATA: type = "lstr_t "; break;
498 case IOP_T_XML: type = "lstr_t "; break;
499 case IOP_T_ENUM:
500 sb_addnc(sb, indent, ' ');
501 sb_addf(sb, "%s__%s__t %s;\n", t_iopc_path_to_c(f->type_path),
502 t_iopc_name_to_c(f->type_name),
503 t_iopc_name_to_c(f->name));
504 return;
505 default:
506 sb_addnc(sb, indent, ' ');
507 sb_addf(sb, "struct %s__%s__t%s%s;\n",
508 t_iopc_path_to_c(f->type_path),
509 t_iopc_name_to_c(f->type_name),
510 type_is_class || f->is_ref ? " *nonnull " : " ",
511 t_iopc_name_to_c(f->name));
512 return;
513 }
514 break;
515 }
516
517 if (old_type) {
518 sb_addf(sb, "#ifndef IOP_ARRAY_T\n");
519 sb_addnc(sb, indent, ' ');
520 sb_addf(sb, "%s%s;\n", old_type, t_iopc_name_to_c(f->name));
521 sb_adds(sb, "#else\n");
522 }
523
524 assert (type);
525 sb_addnc(sb, indent, ' ');
526 sb_addf(sb, "%s%s;\n", type, t_iopc_name_to_c(f->name));
527
528 if (old_type) {
529 sb_adds(sb, "#endif\n");
530 }
531}

533qm_kvec_t(rg, lstr_t, int, qhash_lstr_hash, qhash_lstr_equal);
534static qm_t(rg) range_h_g = QM_INIT_CACHED(rg, range_h_g);
535
536static int iopc_put_range(sb_t *sb, const iop_array_i32_t *tab)
537{
538 qm_t(rg) *h = &range_h_g;
539 lstr_t s = LSTR_INIT((char *)tab->tab, 4 * tab->len);
540 uint32_t pos = qm_reserve(rg, h, &s, 0);
541 int res;
542
543 if (pos & QHASH_COLLISION)
544 return h->values[pos ^ QHASH_COLLISION];
545
546 h->keys[pos] = lstr_dup(s);
547 h->values[pos] = res = qm_len(rg, h);
548 sb_addf(sb, "static int const iop__ranges__%d[] = {\n", res);
549 for (int i = 0; i < tab->len / 2; i++)
550 sb_addf(sb, " %d, %d,\n", tab->tab[2 * i], tab->tab[2 * i + 1]);
551 sb_addf(sb, " %d,\n"
552 "};\n", tab->tab[tab->len - 1]);
553 return res;
554}
555
556static void iopc_put_range_cleanup(void)
557{
558 qm_deep_clear(rg, &range_h_g, lstr_wipe, IGNORE);
559}

561static lstr_t ctype_get_prefix(lstr_t ctype)
562{
563 lstr_t pfx = lstr_dupc(ctype);
564
565 if (expect(lstr_endswith(ctype, LSTR("__t")))) {
566 pfx.len -= 3;
567 }
568 return pfx;
569}

571static void iopc_gen_ctype(sb_t *buf, const qv_t(iopc_attr) *attrs,
572 const char *tbase, iop_type_t type, int class_id)
573{
574 assert (type == IOP_T_STRUCT || type == IOP_T_UNION
575 || type == IOP_T_ENUM);
576
577 tab_for_each_entry(attr, attrs) {
578 if (attr->desc->id == IOPC_ATTR_CTYPE) {
579 tab_for_each_ptr(arg, &attr->args) {
580 lstr_t ctype = arg->v.s;
581 lstr_t pfx;
582
583 pfx = ctype_get_prefix(ctype);
584 sb_addf(buf, "typedef %s__t %*pM;\n", tbase,
585 LSTR_FMT_ARG(ctype));
586 sb_addf(buf, "typedef %s__array_t %*pM__array_t;\n", tbase,
587 LSTR_FMT_ARG(pfx));
588
589 if (type == IOP_T_STRUCT || type == IOP_T_UNION) {
590 sb_addf(buf, "#define %*pM__s %s__s\n",
591 LSTR_FMT_ARG(pfx), tbase);
592 } else
593 if (type == IOP_T_ENUM) {
594 sb_addf(buf, "typedef %s__opt_t %*pM__opt_t;\n",
595 tbase, LSTR_FMT_ARG(pfx));
596 sb_addf(buf, "#define %*pM__e %s__e\n",
597 LSTR_FMT_ARG(pfx), tbase);
598 }
599 if (class_id != -1) {
600 sb_addf(buf, "#define %*pM__class_id %d\n",
601 LSTR_FMT_ARG(pfx), class_id);
602 }
603
604 sb_addc(buf, '\n');
605 }
606 }
607 }

612typedef struct iopc_attr_kind_t {
613 const char *attr_typename;
614 const char *attr_arg_typename;
615 const char *attrs_typename;
616 const char *attrs_var_sfx;
617 const char *ext;
618 int str_gen_type;
619 int int_gen_type;
620 int bool_gen_type;
621 int double_gen_type;
622 int ident_gen_type;
623 int help_type;

795static unsigned iopc_attr_kind_get_gen_type(const iopc_attr_kind_t *attr_kind,
796 iopc_tok_type_t tok_type)
797{
798 switch (tok_type) {
799 case ITOK_STRING:
800 return attr_kind->str_gen_type;
801
802 case ITOK_INTEGER:
803 return attr_kind->int_gen_type;
804
805 case ITOK_BOOL:
806 return attr_kind->bool_gen_type;
807
808 case ITOK_DOUBLE:
809 return attr_kind->double_gen_type;
810
811 case ITOK_IDENT:
812 return attr_kind->ident_gen_type;
813
814 default:
815 assert(false);
816 return 0;
817 }
818}

822
823static void write_string(sb_t *buf, const char *s, const char *escaped_chars)
824{
825 for (;; s++) {
826 const char *c;
827
828 for (c = s; isprint(*c) && *c != '"'; c++) {
829 for (const char *ec = escaped_chars; *ec ; ec++) {
830 if (*c == *ec)
831 goto write_chars;
832 }
833 }
834 write_chars:
835 sb_add(buf, s, c - s);
836 s = c;
837
838 if (!*s)
839 break;
840 sb_addf(buf, "\\%03o", (uint8_t)*s);
841 }
842}
843
844static void write_help_string(sb_t *buf, const char *s)
845{
846 write_string(buf, s, "\\");
847}
848
849#define NAME_FIELD_FMT "%s__%s"
850#define NAME_FIELD_FMT_ARG(_pfx, _ext) _pfx, _ext
851
852#define NAME_HELP_FMT NAME_FIELD_FMT"_help"
853#define NAME_HELP_FMT_ARG(_pfx, _ext) NAME_FIELD_FMT_ARG(_pfx, _ext)
854
855static bool has_help(const qv_t(iopc_dox) *comments)
856{
857 for (int i = 0; i <= IOPC_DOX_TYPE_SIMPLE; i++) {
858 if (iopc_dox_find_type(comments, i)) {
859 return true;
860 }
861 }
862 return false;
863}
864
865static void
866iopc_dump_help(sb_t *buf, const iopc_attr_kind_t *attr_kind,
867 const char *help_var_pfx,
868 const qv_t(iopc_dox) *comments)
869{
870 sb_addf(buf, "static const iop_help_t "NAME_HELP_FMT
871 " = {\n",
872 NAME_HELP_FMT_ARG(help_var_pfx, attr_kind->ext));
873
874 for (int i = 0; i <= IOPC_DOX_TYPE_SIMPLE; i++) {
875 const iopc_dox_t *dox = iopc_dox_find_type(comments, i);
876 lstr_t type;
877
878 if (!dox) {
879 continue;
880 }
881
882 type = iopc_dox_type_to_lstr(i);
883 sb_addf(buf, " .%*pM = ", LSTR_FMT_ARG(type));
884 if (!dox->desc.len) {
885 sb_adds(buf, "LSTR_NULL,\n");
886 } else {
887 sb_adds(buf, "LSTR_IMMED(\"");
888 write_help_string(buf, dox->desc.s);
889 sb_adds(buf, "\"),\n");
890 }
891 }
892 sb_addf(buf, "};\n");
893}

895static void
896iopc_dump_help_ref(sb_t *buf, const iopc_attr_kind_t *attr_kind,
897 const char *help_var_pfx)
898{
899 sb_addf(buf, " {\n"
900 " .type = %d,\n"
901 " .args = (%s[]){ { .v.p = &"NAME_HELP_FMT" } },\n"
902 " },\n",
903 attr_kind->help_type, attr_kind->attr_arg_typename,
904 NAME_HELP_FMT_ARG(help_var_pfx, attr_kind->ext));
905}

963static void
964iopc_enum_dump_tdef_hdr(sb_t *buf, const char *pkg_name,
965 const iopc_enum_t *en)
966{
967 t_scope;
968 const char *tname = t_iopc_name_to_c(en->name);
969 char *tbase = t_fmt("%s__%s", pkg_name, tname);
970 int next_value = 0;
971 lstr_t ns = t_enum_get_prefix(en);
972 int min = INT_MAX;
973 int max = INT_MIN;
974
975 sb_addf(buf, "typedef enum %s__t {\n", tbase);
976
977 tab_for_each_entry(f, &en->values) {
978 sb_addf(buf, " %*pM_%s", LSTR_FMT_ARG(ns), f->name);
979 if (f->value == next_value++) {
980 sb_adds(buf, ",\n");
981 } else {
982 sb_addf(buf, " = %d,\n", f->value);
983 next_value = f->value + 1;
984 }
985 if (f->value > max)
986 max = f->value;
987 if (f->value < min)
988 min = f->value;
989 tab_for_each_entry(attr, &f->attrs) {
990 if (attr->desc->id == IOPC_ATTR_ALIAS) {
991 tab_for_each_entry(alias, &attr->args) {
992 sb_addf(buf, " %*pM_%*pM", LSTR_FMT_ARG(ns),
993 LSTR_FMT_ARG(alias.v.s));
994 sb_addf(buf, " = %*pM_%s,\n", LSTR_FMT_ARG(ns), f->name);
995 }
996 }
997 }
998 }
999 sb_addf(buf, "} %s__t;\n", tbase);
1000 sb_addf(buf,
1001 "typedef IOP_ARRAY_OF(enum %s__t) %s__array_t;\n",
1002 tbase, tbase);
1003 sb_addf(buf,
1004 "#ifdef OPT_OF\n"
1005 "typedef OPT_OF(enum %s__t) %s__opt_t;\n"
1006 "#else\n"
1007 "typedef IOP_OPT_OF(enum %s__t) %s__opt_t;\n"
1008 "#endif\n",
1009 tbase, tbase, tbase, tbase);
1010 sb_addf(buf,
1011 "#define %*pM_count %d\n"
1012 "#define %*pM_min %d\n"
1013 "#define %*pM_max %d\n",
1014 LSTR_FMT_ARG(ns), en->values.len, LSTR_FMT_ARG(ns), min,
1015 LSTR_FMT_ARG(ns), max);
1016 sb_addc(buf, '\n');
1017}

1053static const char *iopc_field_type(const iopc_field_t *f)
1054{
1055 switch (f->kind) {
1056 case IOP_T_U8: return "uint8_t ";
1057 case IOP_T_I8: return "int8_t ";
1058 case IOP_T_U16: return "uint16_t ";
1059 case IOP_T_I16: return "int16_t ";
1060 case IOP_T_U32: return "uint32_t ";
1061 case IOP_T_I32: return "int32_t ";
1062 case IOP_T_U64: return "uint64_t ";
1063 case IOP_T_I64: return "int64_t ";
1064 case IOP_T_BOOL: return "bool ";
1065 case IOP_T_DOUBLE: return "double ";
1066 case IOP_T_STRING: return "lstr_t ";
1067 case IOP_T_DATA: return "lstr_t ";
1068 case IOP_T_XML: return "lstr_t ";
1069 case IOP_T_ENUM: return "enum ";
1070
1071 default:
1072 warn_loc("attribute type not handled for this kind", f->loc);
1073 assert (false);
1074 return NULL;
1075 }
1076}

1116
1117static void iopc_struct_dump_hdr_class(sb_t *buf, iopc_struct_t *st)
1118{
1119 t_scope;
1120 qv_t(iopc_struct) parents;
1121 qv_t(iopc_pkg) parents_pkgs;
1122 int ident;
1123
1124 if (!st->extends.len || st->extends.tab[0]->is_snmp_root) {
1125 sb_adds(buf, " const iop_struct_t *nonnull __vptr;\n");
1126 return;
1127 }
1128
1129 /* Get parents list; last element of vector will be the master class, and
1130 * the first one the nearest parent. */
1131 qv_init(&parents);
1132 qv_init(&parents_pkgs);
1133 do {
1134 qv_append(&parents_pkgs, st->extends.tab[0]->pkg);
1135 st = st->extends.tab[0]->st;
1136 qv_append(&parents, st);
1137 } while (st->extends.len && !st->extends.tab[0]->is_snmp_root);
1138
1139 sb_addnc(buf, 4, ' ');
1140 sb_adds(buf, "union {\n");
1141 sb_addnc(buf, 8, ' ');
1142 sb_addf(buf, "struct %s__%s__t super;\n",
1143 t_iopc_path_to_c(parents_pkgs.tab[0]->name),
1144 t_iopc_name_to_c(parents.tab[0]->name));
1145
1146 /* Print parent structure */
1147 for (ident = 8; ident <= 4 * parents.len + 4; ident += 4) {
1148 sb_addnc(buf, ident, ' ');
1149 sb_adds(buf, "struct {\n");
1150 }
1151 sb_addnc(buf, ident, ' ');
1152 sb_adds(buf, "const iop_struct_t *nonnull __vptr;\n");
1153
1154 tab_for_each_pos_safe(pos, &parents) {
1155 st = parents.tab[pos];
1156 sb_addnc(buf, ident, ' ');
1157 sb_addf(buf, "/* fields of %s__%s__t */\n",
1158 t_iopc_path_to_c(parents_pkgs.tab[pos]->name),
1159 t_iopc_name_to_c(st->name));
1160 iopc_struct_optimize(st);
1161 iopc_struct_dump_fields(buf, ident, &st->fields_in_c_struct_order);
1162 ident -= 4;
1163 sb_addnc(buf, ident, ' ');
1164 sb_adds(buf, "};\n");
1165 }
1166
1167 sb_addnc(buf, 4, ' ');
1168 sb_adds(buf, "};\n");
1169
1170 qv_wipe(&parents);
1171 qv_wipe(&parents_pkgs);
1172}
1173
1174static void iopc_struct_dump_hdr(sb_t *buf, const iopc_pkg_t *pkg,
1175 const char *pkg_name, iopc_struct_t *st,
1176 const char *ns)
1177{
1178 t_scope;
1179 const char *tname = t_iopc_name_to_c(st->name);
1180 char *tbase = t_fmt("%s__%s", ns ?: pkg_name, tname);
1181
1182 assert (st->type != STRUCT_TYPE_UNION);
1183
1184 if (st->c_hdr_written) {
1185 return;
1186 }
1187
1188 st->c_hdr_written = true;
1189 iopc_struct_optimize(st);
1190
1191 if (!iopc_is_snmp_obj(st->type)) {
1192 if (iopc_is_class(st->type) && st->extends.len
1193 && pkg == st->extends.tab[0]->pkg)
1194 {
1195 iopc_struct_dump_hdr(buf, st->extends.tab[0]->pkg, pkg_name,
1196 st->extends.tab[0]->st, ns);
1197 }
1198
1199 sb_addf(buf, "struct %s__t {\n", tbase);
1200
1201 if (iopc_is_class(st->type)) {
1202 iopc_struct_dump_hdr_class(buf, st);
1203 }
1204
1205 if (st->contains_snmp_info) {
1206 iopc_struct_dump_snmp_fields(buf, 4,
1207 &st->fields_in_c_struct_order);
1208 } else {
1209 iopc_struct_dump_fields(buf, 4, &st->fields_in_c_struct_order);
1210 }
1211
1212 sb_adds(buf, "};\n");
1213 }
1214 sb_addf(buf, "EXPORT iop_struct_t const %s__s;\n", tbase);
1215 sb_addf(buf, "EXPORT iop_struct_t const * const nonnull %s__sp;\n",
1216 tbase);
1217 if (iopc_is_class(st->type)) {
1218 sb_addf(buf, "#define %s__class_id %d\n\n", tbase, st->class_id);
1219 iopc_gen_ctype(buf, &st->attrs, tbase, IOP_T_STRUCT, st->class_id);
1220 } else
1221 if (!iopc_is_snmp_st(st->type)) {
1222 iopc_gen_ctype(buf, &st->attrs, tbase, IOP_T_STRUCT, -1);
1223 }
1224}

1228 const iopc_field_t *field)

1241static void iopc_union_dump_tag_cst(sb_t *buf, const char *tbase,
1242 const iopc_struct_t *st)
1243{
1244 /* TODO OMG use a function for that. */
1245#define VOID_TAG_ALIAS(buf, f, tbase, name) \
1246 if (f->kind == IOP_T_VOID && f->repeat == IOP_R_REQUIRED) { \
1247 sb_addf(buf, "#define %*pM__%s__empty_ft %*pM__%s__ft\n", \
1248 LSTR_FMT_ARG(tbase), name, LSTR_FMT_ARG(tbase), name); \
1249 }
1250
1251 sb_addf(buf, "typedef enum %s__tag_t {\n", tbase);
1252 tab_for_each_entry(f, &st->fields_by_tag) {
1253 t_scope;
1254 const char *field_c_name = t_iopc_name_to_c(f->name);
1255
1256 /* Tag of the field (enum) */
1257 sb_addf(buf, " %s__%s__ft = %d,\n", tbase, field_c_name, f->tag);
1258 VOID_TAG_ALIAS(buf, f, LSTR(tbase), field_c_name);
1259 }
1260 sb_addf(buf, "} %s__tag_t;\n", tbase);
1261
1262 tab_for_each_entry(attr, &st->attrs) {
1263 if (attr->desc->id == IOPC_ATTR_CTYPE) {
1264 tab_for_each_ptr(arg, &attr->args) {
1265 lstr_t ctype;
1266
1267 assert (lstr_endswith(arg->v.s, LSTR("__t")));
1268 ctype = LSTR_INIT_V(arg->v.s.s, arg->v.s.len - 3);
1269 sb_addf(buf, "typedef %s__tag_t %*pM__tag_t;\n", tbase,
1270 LSTR_FMT_ARG(ctype));
1271 tab_for_each_entry(f, &st->fields) {
1272 t_scope;
1273 const char *field_c_name = t_iopc_name_to_c(f->name);
1274
1275 sb_addf(buf, "#define %*pM__%s__ft %s__%s__ft\n",
1276 LSTR_FMT_ARG(ctype), field_c_name, tbase,
1277 field_c_name);
1278 VOID_TAG_ALIAS(buf, f, ctype, field_c_name);
1279 }
1280 }
1281 }
1282 }
1283#undef VOID_ALIAS
1284}

1286/* FIXME Too much in common with iopc_union_dump_tag_cst().
1287 * Refactor needed. */
1288static void iopc_union_dump_fdesc_cst(sb_t *buf, const char *tbase,
1289 const iopc_struct_t *st)
1290{
1291 tab_enumerate(pos, f, &st->fields_by_tag) {
1292 t_scope;
1293 sb_addf(buf, "#define %s__%s__fdesc %s__s.fields[%d]\n",
1294 tbase, t_iopc_name_to_c(f->name), tbase, pos);
1295 }
1296
1297 tab_for_each_entry(attr, &st->attrs) {
1298 if (attr->desc->id == IOPC_ATTR_CTYPE) {
1299 tab_for_each_ptr(arg, &attr->args) {
1300 lstr_t ctype;
1301
1302 assert (lstr_endswith(arg->v.s, LSTR("__t")));
1303 ctype = LSTR_INIT_V(arg->v.s.s, arg->v.s.len - 3);
1304
1305 tab_for_each_entry(f, &st->fields_by_tag) {
1306 t_scope;
1307 const char *field_c_name = t_iopc_name_to_c(f->name);
1308
1309 sb_addf(buf, "#define %*pM__%s__fdesc %s__%s__fdesc\n",
1310 LSTR_FMT_ARG(ctype), field_c_name,
1311 tbase, field_c_name);
1312 }
1313 }
1314 }
1315 }

1318static void iopc_union_dump_hdr(sb_t *buf, const char *pkg_name,
1319 iopc_struct_t *st)
1320{
1321 t_scope;
1322 const char *tname = t_iopc_name_to_c(st->name);
1323 char *tbase = t_fmt("%s__%s", pkg_name, tname);
1324
1325 assert (st->type == STRUCT_TYPE_UNION);
1326
1327 iopc_struct_optimize(st);
1328
1329 sb_adds(buf, "/*----- XXX private data, do not use directly -{{{-*/\n");
1330
1331 iopc_union_dump_tag_cst(buf, tbase, st);
1332 sb_addc(buf, '\n');
1333 iopc_union_dump_fdesc_cst(buf, tbase, st);
1334 sb_adds(buf, "/*-}}}-*/\n");
1335
1336 sb_addf(buf, "struct %s__t {\n", tbase);
1337 sb_addf(buf, " %s__tag_t iop_tag;\n", tbase);
1338 sb_addf(buf, " union {\n");
1339 tab_for_each_entry(f, &st->fields_in_c_struct_order) {
1340 pp_field_with_type(buf, f, 8);
1341 }
1342 sb_addf(buf, " };\n"
1343 "};\n"
1344 "EXPORT iop_struct_t const %s__s;\n"
1345 "EXPORT iop_struct_t const * const nonnull %s__sp;\n",
1346 tbase, tbase);
1347
1348 /* Get & copy functions */
1349 sb_addf(buf, "#define %s__get(u, field) "
1350 "IOP_UNION_GET(%s, u, field)\n",
1351 tbase, tbase);
1352
1353 iopc_gen_ctype(buf, &st->attrs, tbase, IOP_T_UNION, -1);
1354}

1356static int iopc_fun_n_aliases(const iopc_fun_t *fun)
1357{
1358 tab_for_each_entry(attr, &fun->attrs) {
1359 if (attr->desc->id == IOPC_ATTR_ALIAS) {
1360 return attr->args.len;
1361 }
1362 }
1363 return 0;
1364}

1366static void
1367iopc_fun_struct_dump_tdef_hdr(sb_t *buf, const char *pkg_name,
1368 const char *ibase, const char *fbase,
1369 const char *fun_type, iopc_fun_struct_t *fun_st)
1370{
1371 if (iopc_fun_struct_is_void(fun_st)) {
1372 sb_addf(buf, "typedef iop__void__t %s_%s__t;\n", fbase, fun_type);

1378 t_scope;
1379
1380 /* When the function argument is just a reference to another
1381 * structure, we just yield several alias using macros */
1382 sb_addf(buf, "typedef %s__%s__t %s_%s__t;\n",
1383 t_iopc_path_to_c(fun_st->existing_struct->type_path),
1384 t_iopc_name_to_c(fun_st->existing_struct->type_name),
1385 fbase, fun_type);
1386 }
1387 }

1421static void
1422iopc_iface_dump_hdr(sb_t *buf, const iopc_pkg_t *pkg,
1423 const char *pkg_name, iopc_iface_t *iface)
1424{
1425 t_scope;
1426 const char *iname = t_iopc_name_to_c(iface->name);
1427 char *ibase = t_fmt("%s__%s", pkg_name, iname);
1428 int j = 0;
1429
1430 if (!iface->funs.len)
1431 return;
1432
1433 sb_addf(buf,
1434 "/*----- interface %s.%s -----*/\n",
1435 iopc_path_dot(pkg->name), iface->name);
1436
1437 tab_for_each_entry(fun, &iface->funs) {
1438 char *fbase = t_fmt("%s__%s", ibase, t_iopc_name_to_c(fun->name));
1439
1440 iopc_fun_struct_dump_hdr(buf, pkg, pkg_name, ibase, &fun->arg);
1441 iopc_fun_struct_dump_hdr(buf, pkg, pkg_name, ibase, &fun->res);
1442 iopc_fun_struct_dump_hdr(buf, pkg, pkg_name, ibase, &fun->exn);
1443
1444 sb_addf(buf,
1445 "#define %s__rpc__tag 0x%04x\n"
1446 "#define %s__rpc__async %d\n"
1447 "#define %s__rpc (%s__if.funs + %d)\n\n",
1448 fbase, fun->tag, fbase, fun->fun_is_async, fbase, ibase, j);
1449 j += 1 + iopc_fun_n_aliases(fun);
1450 }
1451 sb_addf(buf, "EXPORT iop_iface_t const %s__if;\n", ibase);
1452 sb_addf(buf, "EXPORT iop_iface_t const * const nonnull %s__ifp;\n\n",
1453 ibase);
1454}

1500static char const * const repeats[] = {
1501 [IOP_R_OPTIONAL] = "IOP_R_OPTIONAL",
1502 [IOP_R_DEFVAL] = "IOP_R_DEFVAL",
1503 [IOP_R_REQUIRED] = "IOP_R_REQUIRED",
1504 [IOP_R_REPEATED] = "IOP_R_REPEATED",
1505};
1506static char const * const types[] = {
1507#define ITEM(n) [IOP_T_##n] = TOSTR(IOP_T_##n)
1508 ITEM(U8), ITEM(I8),
1509 ITEM(U16), ITEM(I16),
1510 ITEM(U32), ITEM(I32),
1511 ITEM(U64), ITEM(I64),
1512 ITEM(BOOL),
1513 ITEM(ENUM),
1514 ITEM(DOUBLE),
1515 ITEM(STRING),
1516 ITEM(DATA),
1517 ITEM(XML),
1518 ITEM(UNION),
1519 ITEM(STRUCT),
1520 ITEM(VOID),
1521#undef ITEM
1522};

1524static void defval_escape(sb_t *sb, const void *ptr)
1525{
1526 write_string(sb, ptr, "?");
1527}
1528
1529/** Process the value of the flags associated to an IOP field. */
1530static unsigned iopc_field_build_flags(const iopc_field_t *nonnull f,
1531 const iopc_struct_t *nonnull st,
1532 const iopc_attrs_t *nullable attrs)
1533{
1534 unsigned flags = 0;
1535
1536 if (f->is_ref) {
1537 SET_BIT(&flags, IOP_FIELD_IS_REFERENCE);
1538 }
1539 if (attrs && attrs->checkf_name.len) {
1540 SET_BIT(&flags, IOP_FIELD_CHECK_CONSTRAINTS);
1541 }
1542 if (f->snmp_is_from_param || iopc_is_snmp_st(st->type)) {
1543 SET_BIT(&flags, IOP_FIELD_HAS_SNMP_INFO);
1544 }
1545 tab_for_each_entry(attr, &f->attrs) {
1546 if (attr->desc->id == IOPC_ATTR_SNMP_INDEX) {
1547 SET_BIT(&flags, IOP_FIELD_IS_SNMP_INDEX);
1548 } else
1549 if (attr->desc->id == IOPC_ATTR_MIN_OCCURS) {
1550 SET_BIT(&flags, 1 /* IOP_FIELD_NO_EMPTY_ARRAY */);
1551 break;
1552 }
1553 }
1554
1555 return flags;
1556}
1557
1558static void
1559iopc_dump_field_src(sb_t *buf, const iopc_struct_t *st, const char *tbase,
1560 const iopc_field_t *f, const iopc_attrs_t *attrs)
1561{
1562 t_scope;
1563 unsigned flags = 0;
1564 const char *cname = t_iopc_name_to_c(f->name);
1565 iop_type_t kind = f->kind;
1566
1567 /* IOPC fields with types taken from IOP environment cannot be dumped to C
1568 * code. */
1569 assert (!f->has_external_type);
1570
1571 /* If the field is a field of a snmp rpc' struct, it is needed to get the
1572 * real type of the field, which is the one of field_origin */
1573 if (f->snmp_is_from_param) {
1574 kind = f->field_origin->kind;
1575 }
1576
1577 sb_addf(buf,
1578 " {\n"
1579 " .name = LSTR_IMMED(\"%s\"),\n"
1580 " .tag = %d,\n"
1581 " .tag_len = %d,\n"
1582 " .repeat = %s,\n"
1583 " .type = %s,\n",
1584 f->name, f->tag, iopc_tag_len(f->tag),
1585 repeats[f->repeat], types[kind]);
1586
1587 if (!iopc_is_snmp_obj(st->type)) {
1588 if (iopc_struct_is_field_ignored(f)) {
1589 if (st->type == STRUCT_TYPE_UNION) {
1590 assert(st->fields_by_tag.len == st->fields.len);
1591 tab_for_each_entry(f2, &st->fields_by_tag) {
1592 if (!iopc_struct_is_field_ignored(f2)) {
1593 sb_addf(buf,
1594 " .data_offs = offsetof(%s__t, %s),\n",
1595 tbase, t_iopc_name_to_c(f2->name));
1596 break;
1597 }
1598 }
1599 }
1600 } else {
1601 sb_addf(buf,
1602 " .data_offs = offsetof(%s__t, %s),\n",
1603 tbase, cname);
1604 }
1605 }
1606
1607 flags = iopc_field_build_flags(f, st, attrs);
1608 if (flags) {
1609 sb_addf(buf, " .flags = %u,\n", flags);
1610 }
1611
1612 if (f->repeat == IOP_R_DEFVAL) {
1613 t_scope;
1614 sb_t sb;
1615
1616 t_sb_init(&sb, BUFSIZ);
1617 switch (f->kind) {
1618 case IOP_T_ENUM:
1619 sb_addf(buf,
1620 " .u0 = { .defval_enum = %jd },\n",
1621 f->defval.u64);
1622 break;
1623 case IOP_T_I8 ... IOP_T_U64:
1624 sb_addf(buf,
1625 " .u1 = { .defval_u64 = 0x%jx },\n",
1626 f->defval.u64);
1627 break;
1628 case IOP_T_BOOL:
1629 sb_addf(buf,
1630 " .u1 = { .defval_u64 = %s },\n",
1631 f->defval.u64 ? "true" : "false");
1632 break;
1633 case IOP_T_DOUBLE:
1634 sb_addf(buf,
1635 " .u1 = { .defval_d = "DOUBLE_FMT" },\n",
1636 f->defval.d);
1637 break;
1638 case IOP_T_STRING:
1639 case IOP_T_DATA:
1640 case IOP_T_XML:
1641 /* Perform an octal escaping */
1642 defval_escape(&sb, f->defval.ptr);
1643 sb_addf(buf,
1644 " .u0 = { .defval_len = %zd },\n"
1645 " .u1 = { .defval_data = \"%s\" },\n",
1646 strlen(f->defval.ptr), sb.data);
1647 break;
1648
1649 default:
1650 break;
1651 }
1652 }
1653
1654 if (f->kind == IOP_T_STRUCT || f->kind == IOP_T_UNION) {
1655 t_scope;
1656
1657 /* XXX: Fields of type class are ALWAYS pointed, and the size of
1658 * a class type is uninformative (we have to know the real
1659 * instanciated class to know the size), so write the size of
1660 * the pointer in that case, this will simplify some code during
1661 * packing/unpacking. */
1662 sb_addf(buf,
1663 " .size = sizeof(%s__%s__t%s),\n"
1664 " .u1 = { .st_desc = &%s__%s__s },\n",
1665 t_iopc_path_to_c(f->type_path),
1666 t_iopc_name_to_c(f->type_name),
1667 f->struct_def->type == STRUCT_TYPE_CLASS ? " *" : "",
1668 t_iopc_path_to_c(f->type_path),
1669 t_iopc_name_to_c(f->type_name));
1670 } else if (f->repeat == IOP_R_REPEATED) {
1671 /* void arrays only have a length, no data */
1672 if (f->kind != IOP_T_VOID) {
1673 sb_addf(buf,
1674 " .size = fieldsizeof(%s__t, %s.tab[0]),\n",
1675 tbase, cname);
1676 }
1677 } else
1678 if (!iopc_is_snmp_st(st->type)) {
1679 /* required void fields are never physically present */
1680 if (!iopc_struct_is_field_ignored(f)) {
1681 sb_addf(buf,
1682 " .size = fieldsizeof(%s__t, %s),\n",
1683 tbase, cname);
1684 }
1685 }
1686 if (f->kind == IOP_T_ENUM) {
1687 t_scope;
1688
1689 sb_addf(buf,
1690 " .u1 = { .en_desc = &%s__%s__e },\n",
1691 t_iopc_path_to_c(f->type_path),
1692 t_iopc_name_to_c(f->type_name));
1693 }
1694 sb_addf(buf, " },\n");
1695}
1696
1697#define ATTR_HELP(_what) IOP_##_what##_ATTR_HELP_V2
1698
1699static void
1700iopc_dump_static_field_src(sb_t *buf, const iopc_field_t *f, const char *name)
1701{
1702 lstr_t type;
1703 const iopc_attr_kind_t *attr_kind = &iopc_attr_kind_static_field_g;
1704 bool has_attrs;
1705
1706 iopc_dump_attrs(attr_kind, &f->comments, &f->attrs, name, buf,
1707 &has_attrs);
1708
1709 sb_addf(buf,
1710 "static const iop_static_field_t %s = {\n"
1711 " .name = LSTR_IMMED(\"%s\"),\n"
1712 " .value = ",
1713 name, f->name);
1714
1715 switch (f->kind) {
1716 case IOP_T_U8:
1717 case IOP_T_U16:
1718 case IOP_T_U32:
1719 case IOP_T_U64:
1720 sb_addf(buf, "{ .u = %ju },\n", f->defval.u64);
1721 type = LSTR("IOP_T_U64");
1722 break;
1723
1724 case IOP_T_DOUBLE:
1725 sb_addf(buf, "{ .d = %.17e },\n", f->defval.d);
1726 type = LSTR("IOP_T_DOUBLE");
1727 break;
1728
1729 case IOP_T_BOOL:
1730 sb_addf(buf, "{ .b = %s },\n",
1731 f->defval.u64 ? "true" : "false");
1732 type = LSTR("IOP_T_BOOL");
1733 break;
1734
1735 case IOP_T_STRING:
1736 case IOP_T_DATA:
1737 case IOP_T_XML:
1738 sb_adds(buf, "{ .s = LSTR_IMMED(\"");
1739 defval_escape(buf, f->defval.ptr);
1740 sb_adds(buf, "\") },\n");
1741 type = LSTR("IOP_T_STRING");
1742 break;
1743
1744 default:
1745 sb_addf(buf, "{ .i = %jd },\n", f->defval.u64);
1746 type = LSTR("IOP_T_I64");
1747 break;
1748 }
1749 sb_addf(buf, " .type = %*pM,\n", LSTR_FMT_ARG(type));
1750
1751 if (has_help(&f->comments) || has_attrs) {
1752 sb_addf(buf, " .attrs = &%s__%s,\n", name,
1753 attr_kind->attrs_var_sfx);
1754 }
1755
1756 sb_addf(buf, "};\n");
1757}
1758
1759static void
1760iopc_struct_dump_static_fields_src(sb_t *buf, iopc_struct_t *st,
1761 const char *tbase)
1762{
1763 t_scope;
1764 int index_field;
1765
1766 if (unlikely(!st->nb_real_static_fields)) {
1767 return;
1768 }
1769 assert (iopc_is_class(st->type));
1770
1771 sb_addc(buf, '\n');
1772
1773 /* Generate static fields structures */
1774 qv_sort(iopc_field)(&st->static_fields,
1775 ^int (iopc_field_t * const *f1, iopc_field_t * const *f2)
1776 {
1777 return strcmp((*f1)->name, (*f2)->name);
1778 });
1779 index_field = 0;
1780 tab_for_each_entry(f, &st->static_fields) {
1781 if (!f->defval_type) {
1782 continue;
1783 }
1784 iopc_dump_static_field_src(buf, f, t_fmt("%s__static_field_%d",
1785 tbase, index_field));
1786 index_field++;
1787 }
1788
1789 /* generate <tbase>__static_fields */
1790 sb_addf(buf,
1791 "static const iop_static_field_t *%s__static_fields[] = {\n",
1792 tbase);
1793 index_field = 0;
1794 tab_for_each_entry(f, &st->static_fields) {
1795 if (!f->defval_type) {
1796 continue;
1797 }
1798 sb_addf(buf, " &%s__static_field_%d,\n", tbase, index_field);
1799 index_field++;
1800 }
1801 sb_adds(buf, "};\n\n");
1802}

1804int iopc_field_get_signed(const iopc_field_t *f, bool *is_signed)
1805{
1806 switch (f->kind) {
1807 case IOP_T_I8:
1808 case IOP_T_I16:
1809 case IOP_T_I32:
1810 case IOP_T_I64:
1811 case IOP_T_ENUM:
1812 case IOP_T_DOUBLE:
1813 *is_signed = true;
1814 break;
1815 case IOP_T_U8:
1816 case IOP_T_U16:
1817 case IOP_T_U32:
1818 case IOP_T_U64:
1819 case IOP_T_BOOL:
1820 *is_signed = false;
1821 break;
1822 default:
1823 throw_error("expected numerical type, got %d", f->kind);
1824 }
1825
1826 return 0;
1827}

1836
1837/* Dump a generic attribute */
1838static void iopc_dump_gen_attr(sb_t *buf, const iopc_attr_t *attr,
1839 unsigned type)
1840{
1841 SB_1k(tmp);
1842 assert (attr->args.len == 1);
1843
1844 /* Generic attributes have only one argument, their values. But we
1845 * want to write two arguments in the generated .c file: the name of
1846 * the attribute, and its value
1847 */
1848
1849 /* First argument: name of the generic attribute */
1850 sb_addf(buf,
1851 LVL1 "{\n"
1852 LVL1 " .type = %d,\n"
1853 LVL1 " .args = (iop_field_attr_arg_t[]){ { .v.s = LSTR_IMMED(\"%*pM\") }, ",
1854 type, LSTR_FMT_ARG(attr->real_name));
1855
1856 /* Second argument: value of the generic attribute */
1857 switch (attr->args.tab[0].type) {
1858 case ITOK_IDENT:
1859 /* JSON object */
1860 sb_add_slashes(&tmp, attr->args.tab[0].v.s.s,
1861 attr->args.tab[0].v.s.len, "\"", "\"");
1862 sb_addf(buf, "{.v.s = LSTR_IMMED(\"%*pM\") } },\n",
1863 SB_FMT_ARG(&tmp));
1864 break;
1865 case ITOK_STRING:
1866 sb_add_slashes(&tmp, attr->args.tab[0].v.s.s,
1867 attr->args.tab[0].v.s.len,
1868 "\a\b\e\t\n\v\f\r'\"", "abetnvfr'\"");
1869 sb_addf(buf, "{.v.s = LSTR_IMMED(\"%*pM\") } },\n",
1870 SB_FMT_ARG(&tmp));
1871 break;
1872 case ITOK_BOOL:
1873 case ITOK_INTEGER:
1874 sb_addf(buf,"{ .v.i64 = %jdUL } },\n",
1875 IOPC_ATTR_GET_ARG_V(int64_t, &attr->args.tab[0]));
1876 break;
1877 case ITOK_DOUBLE:
1878 sb_addf(buf, "{ .v.d = "DOUBLE_FMT" } },\n",
1879 IOPC_ATTR_GET_ARG_V(double, &attr->args.tab[0]));
1880 break;
1881
1882 default:
1883 assert(false);
1884 return;
1885 }
1886
1887 sb_addf(buf,
1888 LVL1 "},\n");
1889
1890 sb_wipe(&tmp);
1891}

1893static void iopc_dump_attrs_ref_body(const iopc_attr_kind_t *attr_kind,
1894 const char *tbase,
1895 lstr_t body, bool is_array, sb_t *buf)
1896{
1897 sb_addf(buf, "static const %s %s__%s",
1898 attr_kind->attrs_typename, tbase, attr_kind->attrs_var_sfx);
1899 if (is_array) {
1900 sb_adds(buf, "[] = {\n");
1901 } else {
1902 sb_adds(buf, " = ");
1903 }
1904 sb_add_lstr(buf, body);
1905 if (is_array) {
1906 sb_adds(buf, "};\n");
1907 }
1908}
1909
1910/** Dump the attributes table associated to a given object.
1911 *
1912 * \param[in] comments Comments associated to the object. They may be
1913 * converted into help attributes.
1914 *
1915 * \param[in] attrs Attributes found around the object. If null, then only
1916 * the help attributes extracted from the comments will be
1917 * dumped.
1918 *
1919 * \param[out] attrs_flags Flags to use in the 'attrs' structure associted to
1920 * the object.
1921 *
1922 * \param[out] attrs_cnt Number of attributes dumped.
1923 */
1924static void iopc_dump_attr_table(const iopc_attr_kind_t *attr_kind,
1925 const qv_t(iopc_dox) *comments,
1926 const qv_t(iopc_attr) *nullable attrs,
1927 const char *var_name_pfx,
1928 sb_t *buf, unsigned *attrs_flags,
1929 int *attrs_cnt)
1930{
1931 SB_1k(attrs_body);
1932 unsigned nbr_attrs = 0;
1933 unsigned flags = 0;
1934
1935 if (has_help(comments)) {
1936 iopc_dump_help_and_ref(buf, &attrs_body, attr_kind,
1937 var_name_pfx, comments);
1938 SET_BIT(&flags, attr_kind->help_type);
1939 nbr_attrs++;
1940 }
1941
1942 if (attrs) {
1943 tab_for_each_entry(attr, attrs) {
1944 unsigned gen_type;
1945
1946 if (attr->desc->id != IOPC_ATTR_GENERIC) {
1947 continue;
1948 }
1949
1950 gen_type = iopc_attr_kind_get_gen_type(attr_kind,
1951 attr->args.tab[0].type);
1952 iopc_dump_gen_attr(&attrs_body, attr, gen_type);
1953 if (attr_kind->write_gen_attr_flags) {
1954 SET_BIT(&flags, gen_type);
1955 }
1956 nbr_attrs++;
1957 }
1958 }
1959
1960 if (nbr_attrs > 0) {
1961 iopc_dump_attr_table_head(buf, attr_kind, var_name_pfx);
1962 sb_addsb(buf, &attrs_body);
1963 sb_addf(buf, "};\n");
1964 }
1965
1966 *attrs_cnt = nbr_attrs;
1967 *attrs_flags = flags;
1968}
1969
1970/** Dump the attributes associated to a given object.
1971 *
1972 * Dump the attribute table and the 'attrs' structure associated to the
1973 * object.
1974 */
1975static void iopc_dump_attrs(const iopc_attr_kind_t *attr_kind,
1976 const qv_t(iopc_dox) *comments,
1977 const qv_t(iopc_attr) *nullable attrs,
1978 const char *var_name_pfx,
1979 sb_t *buf, bool *has_attrs)
1980{
1981 int nbr_attrs;
1982 unsigned flags;
1983
1984 iopc_dump_attr_table(attr_kind, comments, attrs, var_name_pfx, buf,
1985 &flags, &nbr_attrs);
1986 if (nbr_attrs > 0) {
1987 /* Write the 'attrs' structure containing the attributes. */
1988 SB_1k(attrs_ref_body);
1989
1990 iopc_dump_attrs_ref(&attrs_ref_body, flags, nbr_attrs, var_name_pfx,
1991 false, attr_kind->ext);
1992 iopc_dump_attrs_ref_body(attr_kind, var_name_pfx,
1993 LSTR_SB_V(&attrs_ref_body), false, buf);
1994 }
1995 if (has_attrs) {
1996 *has_attrs = !!nbr_attrs;
1997 }
1998}

2002static int
2003iopc_dump_fieldval_loop(sb_t *buf, const iopc_field_t *f)
2004{
2005 t_scope;
2006 const char *type;
2007
2008 sb_adds(buf, LVL1 "for (int j = 0; j < n; j++) {\n");
2009
2010 switch (f->kind) {
2011 case IOP_T_U8: type = "uint8_t "; break;
2012 case IOP_T_I8: type = "int8_t "; break;
2013 case IOP_T_U16: type = "uint16_t "; break;
2014 case IOP_T_I16: type = "int16_t "; break;
2015 case IOP_T_U32: type = "uint32_t "; break;
2016 case IOP_T_I32: type = "int32_t "; break;
2017 case IOP_T_U64: type = "uint64_t "; break;
2018 case IOP_T_I64: type = "int64_t "; break;
2019 case IOP_T_BOOL: type = "bool "; break;
2020 case IOP_T_DOUBLE: type = "double "; break;
2021 case IOP_T_STRING: type = "lstr_t "; break;
2022 case IOP_T_DATA: type = "lstr_t "; break;
2023 case IOP_T_XML: type = "lstr_t "; break;
2024 case IOP_T_ENUM:
2025 sb_addf(buf, LVL2 "%s__%s__t val = IOP_FIELD(int32_t, ptr, j);\n\n",
2026 t_iopc_path_to_c(f->type_path),
2027 t_iopc_name_to_c(f->type_name));
2028 return 0;
2029
2030 case IOP_T_UNION: {
2031 const char *type_cname;
2032 const char *type_path;
2033
2034 type_cname = t_iopc_name_to_c(f->type_name);
2035 type_path = t_iopc_path_to_c(f->type_path);
2036 sb_addf(buf, LVL2
2037 "%s__%s__t *val = &IOP_FIELD(%s__%s__t, ptr, j);\n\n",
2038 type_path, type_cname,
2039 type_path, type_cname);
2040 return 0;
2041 }
2042
2043 default:
2044 throw_error("constraints not supported for fields of kind %d",
2045 f->kind);
2046 }
2047 sb_addf(buf, LVL2 "%s val = IOP_FIELD(%s, ptr, j);\n\n",
2048 type, type);
2049 return 0;
2050}

2082static inline int get_char(pstream_t *ps, lstr_t *s) {
2083 int c, d;
2084
2085 PS_CHECK(c = ps_getc(ps));
2086 if (c == '\\') {
2087 /* escaped character */
2088 PS_CHECK(d = ps_getc(ps));
2089 switch (d) {
2090 case '\\':
2091 *s = LSTR("\\\\");
2092 return 0;
2093 case '|': case '.': case '-': case '^': case '?':
2094 case '*': case '+': case '{': case '}': case '(': case ')':
2095 case '[': case ']':
2096 *s = LSTR_INIT_V(ps->s - 1, 1);
2097 return 0;
2098 default:
2099 return -1;
2100 }
2101 } else {
2102 switch (c) {
2103 /* unsupported regexp special char */
2104 case '|': case '.': case '-': case '^': case '?':
2105 case '*': case '+': case '{': case '}': case '(': case ')':
2106 case '[': case ']':
2107 return -1;
2108 default:
2109 *s = LSTR_INIT_V(ps->s - 1, 1);
2110 return 0;
2111 }
2112 }
2113}

2117
2118static int
2119iopc_dump_pattern(sb_t *sb, const iopc_attr_t *attr, const iopc_field_t *f)
2120{
2121
2122 SB_1k(sbcase);
2123 SB_1k(cpattern);
2124 SB_1k(error);
2125 bool negative = false;
2126 lstr_t pattern = attr->args.tab[0].v.s;
2127 pstream_t ps = ps_initlstr(&pattern);
2128
2129 PS_WANT(ps_getc(&ps) == '[');
2130
2131 PS_WANT(ps_has(&ps, 2));
2132 PS_WANT(ps.b_end[-2] == ']' && ps.b_end[-1] == '*');
2133 PS_CHECK(ps_shrink(&ps, 2));
2134
2135 PS_WANT(!ps_done(&ps));
2136 if (*ps.b == '^') {
2137 negative = true;
2138 ps_skip(&ps, 1);
2139 PS_WANT(!ps_done(&ps));
2140 }
2141
2142 while (!ps_done(&ps)) {
2143 lstr_t start = LSTR_EMPTY_V;
2144
2145 PS_CHECK(get_char(&ps, &start));
2146
2147 if (ps_has(&ps, 1) && *ps.b == '-') {
2148 lstr_t end = LSTR_EMPTY_V;
2149
2150 __ps_skip(&ps, 1);
2151 PS_CHECK(get_char(&ps, &end));
2152 sb_addf(&sbcase, LVL4 "case '%*pM' ... '%*pM':\n",
2153 LSTR_FMT_ARG(start), LSTR_FMT_ARG(end));
2154 } else {
2155 sb_addf(&sbcase, LVL4 "case '%*pM':\n", LSTR_FMT_ARG(start));
2156 }
2157 }
2158
2159 sb_add_slashes(&cpattern, pattern.s, pattern.len, "\\", "\\");
2160
2161 sb_addf(&error,
2162 LVL5 "iop_set_err(\"violation of constraint %%s (%%s) "
2163 "on field %%s: %%*pM\",\n"
2164 LVL5 " \"%*pM\", \"%*pM\", \"%s\", LSTR_FMT_ARG(val));\n"
2165 LVL5 "return -1;\n",
2166 LSTR_FMT_ARG(attr->desc->name),
2167 cpattern.len, cpattern.data, f->name);
2168
2169 sb_addf(sb,
2170 LVL2 "for (int c = 0; c < val.len; c++) {\n"
2171 LVL3 "switch (val.s[c]) {\n"
2172 "%*pM"
2173 "%s"
2174 LVL4 "default:\n"
2175 "%s"
2176 LVL3 "}\n"
2177 LVL2 "}\n",
2178 sbcase.len, sbcase.data, negative ? error.data : LVL5 "break;\n",
2179 negative ? LVL5 "break;\n" : error.data);
2180
2181 sb_wipe(&error);
2182 sb_wipe(&sbcase);
2183 sb_wipe(&cpattern);
2184 return 0;
2185}

2187static void
2188iopc_dump_case_allow(sb_t *sb, const char *elem_name,
2189 const iopc_attr_t *attr, const iopc_field_t *f)
2190{
2191 bool is_allow = (attr->desc->id == IOPC_ATTR_ALLOW);
2192 bool allowed = !is_allow;
2193
2194 tab_for_each_ptr(arg, &attr->args) {
2195 if (strequal(elem_name, arg->v.s.s)) {
2196 allowed = !allowed;
2197 break;
2198 }
2199 }
2200
2201 if (allowed) {
2202 sb_addf(sb, LVL2 " break;\n");
2203 } else {
2204 sb_addf(sb, LVL2 " iop_set_err(\"violation of constraint %s "
2205 "(%s) on field %s\");\n"
2206 LVL2 " return -1;\n",
2207 is_allow ? "allow" : "disallow", elem_name, f->name);
2208 }
2209}

2261static int64_t merge_int64(const iopc_attr_t *attr)
2262{
2263 int64_t ret;
2264
2265 switch (attr->desc->id) {
2266 case IOPC_ATTR_MIN_OCCURS:
2267 case IOPC_ATTR_MIN_LENGTH:
2268 case IOPC_ATTR_MIN:
2269 ret = INT64_MIN;
2270 tab_for_each_ptr(arg, &attr->args) {
2271 ret = MAX(ret, IOPC_ATTR_GET_ARG_V(int64_t, arg));
2272 }
2273 break;
2274
2275 case IOPC_ATTR_MAX_OCCURS:
2276 case IOPC_ATTR_MAX_LENGTH:
2277 case IOPC_ATTR_MAX:
2278 ret = INT64_MAX;
2279 tab_for_each_ptr(arg, &attr->args) {
2280 ret = MIN(ret, IOPC_ATTR_GET_ARG_V(int64_t, arg));
2281 }
2282 break;
2283
2284 case IOPC_ATTR_LENGTH:
2285 assert (attr->args.len == 1);
2286 ret = attr->args.tab[0].v.i64;
2287 break;
2288
2289 default:
2290 e_panic("attribute type not handled in `int64`");
2291 }
2292 return ret;
2293}

2345static int iopc_dump_minmax(sb_t *sb, int cmp, const iopc_attr_t *attr,
2346 const iopc_field_t *f)
2347{
2348 bool is_signed;
2349
2350#define GEN_TEST(fmt1, fmt2, type) \
2351 do { \
2352 sb_addf(sb, \
2353 LVL2 "if (val %c " fmt1 ") {\n" \
2354 LVL3 "if (n > 1) {\n" \
2355 \
2356 LVL4 "iop_set_err(\"violation of constraint %%s (" fmt2 ") " \
2357 "on field %%s[%%d]: val=" fmt2 "\",\n" \
2358 LVL4 " \"%*pM\", (" type ")" fmt1 ", \"%s\", j, " \
2359 "(" type ")val);\n" \
2360 \
2361 LVL3 "} else {\n" \
2362 \
2363 LVL4 "iop_set_err(\"violation of constraint %%s (" fmt2 ") " \
2364 "on field %%s: val=" fmt2 "\",\n" \
2365 LVL4 " \"%*pM\", (" type ")" fmt1 ", \"%s\", " \
2366 "(" type ")val);\n" \
2367 \
2368 LVL3 "}\n" \
2369 \
2370 LVL3 "return -1;\n" \
2371 LVL2 "}\n", \
2372 cmp, v, LSTR_FMT_ARG(attr->desc->name), v, f->name, \
2373 LSTR_FMT_ARG(attr->desc->name), v, f->name); \
2374 } while (0)
2375
2376 RETHROW(iopc_field_get_signed(f, &is_signed));
2377 if (f->kind == IOP_T_DOUBLE) {
2378 double v = merge_double(attr);
2379
2380 GEN_TEST("%.17e", "%%.17e", "double");
2381 } else
2382 if (is_signed) {
2383 int64_t v = merge_int64(attr);
2384
2385 GEN_TEST("%jdLL", "%%jd", "int64_t");
2386 } else {
2387 uint64_t v = merge_uint64(attr);
2388
2389 GEN_TEST("%juULL", "%%ju", "uint64_t");
2390 }
2391#undef GEN_TEST
2392 return 0;
2393}

2396iopc_dump_non_zero(sb_t *sb, const iopc_attr_t *attr, const iopc_field_t *f)
2397{
2398 sb_addf(sb,
2399 LVL2 "if (val == 0) {\n"
2400 LVL3 "if (n > 1) {\n"
2401
2402 LVL4 "iop_set_err(\"violation of constraint %%s on field %%s[%%d]\",\n"
2403 LVL4 " \"%*pM\", \"%s\", j);\n"
2404
2405 LVL3 "} else {\n"
2406
2407 LVL4 "iop_set_err(\"violation of constraint %%s on field %%s\",\n"
2408 LVL4 " \"%*pM\", \"%s\");\n"
2409
2410 LVL3 "}\n"
2411
2412 LVL3 "return -1;\n"
2413 LVL2 "}\n",
2414 LSTR_FMT_ARG(attr->desc->name), f->name,
2415 LSTR_FMT_ARG(attr->desc->name), f->name);
2416}

2466static int iopc_dump_field_attr(iopc_attr_t *attr, unsigned type,
2467 sb_t *sb, iopc_attrs_t *attrs,
2468 const iopc_field_t *f)
2469{
2470 bool is_signed;
2471 SB_1k(pattern);
2472
2473 SET_BIT(&attrs->flags, type);
2474 attrs->attrs_len++;
2475
2476 switch (attr->desc->id) {
2477 case IOPC_ATTR_MIN_OCCURS:
2478 case IOPC_ATTR_MAX_OCCURS:
2479 case IOPC_ATTR_MIN_LENGTH:
2480 case IOPC_ATTR_MAX_LENGTH:
2481 case IOPC_ATTR_LENGTH:
2482 sb_addf(sb,
2483 LVL1 "{\n"
2484 LVL1 " .type = %d,\n"
2485 LVL1 " .args = (iop_field_attr_arg_t[]){ { .v.i64 = %jdLL } },\n"
2486 LVL1 "},\n",
2487 type, merge_int64(attr));
2488 break;
2489
2490 case IOPC_ATTR_PATTERN:
2491 assert (attr->args.tab[0].type == ITOK_STRING);
2492 assert (attr->args.len == 1);
2493 sb_add_slashes(&pattern, attr->args.tab[0].v.s.s,
2494 attr->args.tab[0].v.s.len, "\\", "\\");
2495 sb_addf(sb,
2496 LVL1 "{\n"
2497 LVL1 " .type = %d,\n"
2498 LVL1 " .args = (iop_field_attr_arg_t[]){ { .v.s = LSTR_IMMED(\"%*pM\") } },\n"
2499 LVL1 "},\n",
2500 type, pattern.len, pattern.data);
2501 break;
2502
2503 case IOPC_ATTR_MIN:
2504 case IOPC_ATTR_MAX:
2505 RETHROW(iopc_field_get_signed(f, &is_signed));
2506 if (f->kind == IOP_T_DOUBLE) {
2507 sb_addf(sb,
2508 LVL1 "{\n"
2509 LVL1 " .type = %d,\n"
2510 LVL1 " .args = (iop_field_attr_arg_t[]){ { .v.d = %.17e } },\n"
2511 LVL1 "},\n",
2512 type, merge_double(attr));
2513 } else
2514 if (is_signed) {
2515 sb_addf(sb,
2516 LVL1 "{\n"
2517 LVL1 " .type = %d,\n"
2518 LVL1 " .args = (iop_field_attr_arg_t[]){ { .v.i64 = %jdLL } },\n"
2519 LVL1 "},\n",
2520 type, merge_int64(attr));
2521 } else {
2522 sb_addf(sb,
2523 LVL1 "{\n"
2524 LVL1 " .type = %d,\n"
2525 LVL1 " .args = (iop_field_attr_arg_t[]){ { .v.i64 = %juULL } },\n"
2526 LVL1 "},\n",
2527 type, merge_uint64(attr));
2528 }
2529 break;
2530
2531 case IOPC_ATTR_GENERIC:
2532 iopc_dump_gen_attr(sb, attr, type);
2533 break;
2534
2535 default:
2536 e_panic("should not happen");
2537 }
2538
2539 sb_wipe(&pattern);
2540 return 0;
2541}

2558static int
2559iopc_dump_field_attrs(sb_t *buf, const iopc_struct_t *st, const char *tbase,
2560 const iopc_field_t *f, iopc_attrs_t *attrs)
2561{
2562 t_scope;
2563 SB_1k(attrs_body);
2564 SB_1k(checkf_body);
2565 SB_1k(checkf_loopbody);
2566 const char *cname = t_iopc_name_to_c(f->name);
2567 const char *var_pfx = t_fmt("%s__%s", tbase, cname);
2568 int type;
2569
2570 iopc_dump_help_and_ref(buf, &attrs_body, &iopc_attr_kind_field_g,
2571 var_pfx, &f->comments);
2572 if (has_help(&f->comments)) {
2573 attrs->attrs_len++;
2574 SET_BIT(&attrs->flags, ATTR_HELP(FIELD));
2575 }
2576
2577 tab_for_each_entry(attr, &f->attrs) {
2578 switch (attr->desc->id) {
2579
2580 case IOPC_ATTR_CDATA:
2581 SET_BIT(&attrs->flags, IOP_FIELD_CDATA);
2582 break;
2583
2584 case IOPC_ATTR_MIN_OCCURS:
2585 iopc_dump_minmax_occurs(&checkf_body, '<', attr, f);
2586 RETHROW(iopc_dump_field_attr(attr, IOP_FIELD_MIN_OCCURS,
2587 &attrs_body, attrs, f));
2588 break;
2589 case IOPC_ATTR_MAX_OCCURS:
2590 iopc_dump_minmax_occurs(&checkf_body, '>', attr, f);
2591 RETHROW(iopc_dump_field_attr(attr, IOP_FIELD_MAX_OCCURS,
2592 &attrs_body, attrs, f));
2593 break;
2594
2595 case IOPC_ATTR_MIN_LENGTH:
2596 iopc_dump_minmax_length(&checkf_loopbody, "<", attr, f);
2597 RETHROW(iopc_dump_field_attr(attr, IOP_FIELD_MIN_LENGTH,
2598 &attrs_body, attrs, f));
2599 break;
2600
2601 case IOPC_ATTR_MAX_LENGTH:
2602 iopc_dump_minmax_length(&checkf_loopbody, ">", attr, f);
2603 RETHROW(iopc_dump_field_attr(attr, IOP_FIELD_MAX_LENGTH,
2604 &attrs_body, attrs, f));
2605 break;
2606
2607 case IOPC_ATTR_LENGTH:
2608 iopc_dump_minmax_length(&checkf_loopbody, "!=", attr, f);
2609 RETHROW(iopc_dump_field_attr(attr, IOP_FIELD_MIN_LENGTH,
2610 &attrs_body, attrs, f));
2611 RETHROW(iopc_dump_field_attr(attr, IOP_FIELD_MAX_LENGTH,
2612 &attrs_body, attrs, f));
2613 break;
2614
2615 case IOPC_ATTR_PATTERN:
2616 if (iopc_dump_pattern(&checkf_loopbody, attr, f) < 0) {
2617 throw_error("unsupported pattern: %*pM",
2618 LSTR_FMT_ARG(attr->args.tab[0].v.s));
2619 }
2620 RETHROW(iopc_dump_field_attr(attr, IOP_FIELD_PATTERN, &attrs_body,
2621 attrs, f));
2622 break;
2623
2624 case IOPC_ATTR_MIN:
2625 RETHROW(iopc_dump_minmax(&checkf_loopbody, '<', attr, f));
2626 RETHROW(iopc_dump_field_attr(attr, IOP_FIELD_MIN, &attrs_body,
2627 attrs, f));
2628 break;
2629 case IOPC_ATTR_MAX:
2630 RETHROW(iopc_dump_minmax(&checkf_loopbody, '>', attr, f));
2631 RETHROW(iopc_dump_field_attr(attr, IOP_FIELD_MAX, &attrs_body,
2632 attrs, f));
2633 break;
2634 case IOPC_ATTR_NON_EMPTY:
2635 iopc_dump_non_empty(&checkf_loopbody, attr, f);
2636 SET_BIT(&attrs->flags, IOP_FIELD_NON_EMPTY);
2637 break;
2638 case IOPC_ATTR_NON_ZERO:
2639 iopc_dump_non_zero(&checkf_loopbody, attr, f);
2640 SET_BIT(&attrs->flags, IOP_FIELD_NON_ZERO);
2641 break;
2642 case IOPC_ATTR_ALLOW:
2643 case IOPC_ATTR_DISALLOW:
2644 iopc_dump_allow(&checkf_loopbody, attr, f);
2645 break;
2646
2647 case IOPC_ATTR_PRIVATE:
2648 SET_BIT(&attrs->flags, IOP_FIELD_PRIVATE);
2649 break;
2650
2651 case IOPC_ATTR_GENERIC:
2652 type = iopc_attr_kind_get_gen_type(&iopc_attr_kind_field_g,
2653 attr->args.tab[0].type);
2654 RETHROW(iopc_dump_field_attr(attr, type, &attrs_body, attrs, f));
2655 break;
2656
2657 case IOPC_ATTR_DEPRECATED:
2658 SET_BIT(&attrs->flags, IOP_FIELD_DEPRECATED);
2659 break;
2660
2661 default:
2662 break;
2663 }
2664 }
2665
2666 if (st->contains_snmp_info || iopc_is_snmp_st(st->type)) {
2667 iopc_dump_snmp_field_attr(&attrs_body, attrs, tbase, cname);
2668 SET_BIT(&attrs->flags, IOP_FIELD_SNMP_INFO);
2669 }
2670
2671 if (checkf_body.len || checkf_loopbody.len) {
2672 attrs->checkf_name = lstr_fmt("%s__%s__check", tbase, cname);
2673
2674 sb_addf(buf,
2675 "static int %*pM(const void *ptr, int n)\n"
2676 "{\n",
2677 LSTR_FMT_ARG(attrs->checkf_name));
2678 sb_addsb(buf, &checkf_body);
2679 if (checkf_loopbody.len) {
2680 RETHROW(iopc_dump_fieldval_loop(buf, f));
2681 sb_addsb(buf, &checkf_loopbody);
2682 sb_adds(buf, " }\n");
2683 }
2684 sb_adds(buf,
2685 " return 0;\n"
2686 "}\n");
2687 }
2688 if (attrs_body.len) {
2689 attrs->attrs_name = lstr_fmt("%s__%s__attrs", tbase, cname);
2690
2691 sb_addf(buf,
2692 "static iop_field_attr_t const %*pM[] = {\n",
2693 LSTR_FMT_ARG(attrs->attrs_name));
2694 sb_addsb(buf, &attrs_body);
2695 sb_adds(buf,
2696 "};\n");
2697 }
2698
2699 return 0;
2700}

2702/** XXX: sb_na buffer where to write attributes other than IOPC_ATTR_ALIAS
2703 * sb_alias buffer where to write attribute IOPC_ATTR_ALIAS
2704 */
2705static void
2706iopc_dump_rpc_attr(iopc_attr_t *attr, sb_t *sb_na, sb_t *sb_alias,
2707 iopc_attrs_t *attrs, const char *ibase,
2708 unsigned *n_func_and_alias)
2709{
2710 unsigned type = 0;
2711
2712 switch (attr->desc->id) {
2713 case IOPC_ATTR_ALIAS:
2714 type = IOP_RPC_ALIAS;
2715 tab_for_each_entry(arg, &attr->args) {
2716 sb_addf(sb_alias,
2717 LVL1 "{\n"
2718 LVL1 " .type = %d,\n"
2719 LVL1 " .args = (iop_rpc_attr_arg_t[]){ { .v.p = (void*)&%s__if_funs[%u] } },\n"
2720 LVL1 "},\n",
2721 type, ibase, *n_func_and_alias);
2722 (*n_func_and_alias)++;
2723 attrs->attrs_len++;
2724 }
2725 break;
2726 case IOPC_ATTR_GENERIC:
2727 type = iopc_attr_kind_get_gen_type(&iopc_attr_kind_rpc_g,
2728 attr->args.tab[0].type);
2729 iopc_dump_gen_attr(sb_na, attr, type);
2730 attrs->attrs_len++;
2731 break;
2732 default:
2733 e_panic("should not happen");
2734 }
2735 SET_BIT(&attrs->flags, type);
2736}

2760static void
2761iopc_dump_rpc_attrs(sb_t *buf, const char *tbase, const iopc_fun_t *f,
2762 iopc_attrs_t *attrs, unsigned *n_func_and_alias)
2763{
2764 t_scope;
2765 SB_1k(attrs_body);
2766 SB_1k(attrs_body_alias);
2767 const char *cname = t_iopc_name_to_c(f->name);
2768 const char *var_pfx = t_fmt("%s__%s", tbase, cname);
2769
2770 iopc_dump_help_and_ref(buf, &attrs_body, &iopc_attr_kind_rpc_g, var_pfx,
2771 &f->comments);
2772 if (has_help(&f->comments)) {
2773 SET_BIT(&attrs->flags, ATTR_HELP(RPC));
2774 attrs->attrs_len++;
2775 }
2776
2777 iopc_dump_fun_struct_attrs(buf, &iopc_attr_kind_rpc_arg_g, tbase, cname,
2778 &f->arg, attrs, &attrs_body);
2779 iopc_dump_fun_struct_attrs(buf, &iopc_attr_kind_rpc_res_g, tbase, cname,
2780 &f->res, attrs, &attrs_body);
2781 iopc_dump_fun_struct_attrs(buf, &iopc_attr_kind_rpc_exn_g, tbase, cname,
2782 &f->exn, attrs, &attrs_body);
2783
2784 tab_for_each_entry(attr, &f->attrs) {
2785 iopc_dump_rpc_attr(attr, &attrs_body, &attrs_body_alias, attrs, tbase,
2786 n_func_and_alias);
2787 }
2788 if (!attrs->attrs_len)
2789 return;
2790
2791 attrs->attrs_name = lstr_fmt("%s__%s__attrs", tbase, cname);
2792
2793 if (attrs_body.len && attrs_body_alias.len) {
2794 /** dump attributes other than aliases, used by aliased functions */
2795 sb_addf(buf, "static iop_rpc_attr_t const %*pM_na[] = {\n",
2796 LSTR_FMT_ARG(attrs->attrs_name));
2797 sb_addsb(buf, &attrs_body);
2798 sb_adds(buf, "};\n");
2799 }
2800
2801 sb_addsb(&attrs_body, &attrs_body_alias);
2802 sb_wipe(&attrs_body_alias);
2803
2804 /** dump all attributes */
2805 sb_addf(buf,
2806 "static iop_rpc_attr_t const %*pM[] = {\n",
2807 LSTR_FMT_ARG(attrs->attrs_name));
2808 sb_addsb(buf, &attrs_body);
2809 sb_adds(buf,
2810 "};\n");
2811 sb_wipe(&attrs_body);
2812}

2858/* FIXME Almost a duplicate from t_iopc_struct_build_ranges. */
2859/** Build the range used to associate an enum value to the associated element.
2860 */
2861static iop_array_i32_t mp_iopc_enum_build_ranges(mem_pool_t *mp,
2862 const iopc_enum_t *en)
2863{
2864 qv_t(i32) t;
2865
2866 mp_qv_init(mp, &t, 2 * en->values.len + 1);
2867 for (int i = 0, last_enum = 0; i < en->values.len; i++) {
2868 iopc_enum_field_t *f = en->values.tab[i];
2869
2870 if (!i || ++last_enum != f->value) {
2871 qv_append(&t, i);
2872 qv_append(&t, f->value);
2873 last_enum = f->value;
2874 }
2875 }
2876 qv_append(&t, en->values.len);
2877 mp_realloc_from(mp, &t.tab, t.size, t.len);
2878
2879 return IOP_TYPED_ARRAY_TAB(i32, &t);
2880}
2881
2882static void
2883iopc_enum_dump_src(sb_t *buf, const iopc_pkg_t *pkg,
2884 const char *pkg_name, iopc_enum_t *en)
2885{
2886 t_scope;
2887 SB_1k(values_attrs_body);
2888 char *tbase = t_fmt("%s__%s", pkg_name, t_iopc_name_to_c(en->name));
2889 int range;
2890 unsigned flags = 0;
2891 bool has_attrs;
2892 iop_array_i32_t t;
2893 bool values_have_attributes = false;
2894 uint16_t alias_count = 0;
2895
2896 qv_sort(iopc_enum_field)(&en->values,
2897 ^int (iopc_enum_field_t * const *f1,
2898 iopc_enum_field_t * const *f2) {
2899 return CMP((*f1)->value, (*f2)->value);
2900 });
2901 sb_addf(buf,
2902 "/* Enum %s.%s {""{{ */\n"
2903 "\n"
2904 "static int const %s__values[] = {\n",
2905 iopc_path_dot(pkg->name), en->name, tbase);
2906 tab_for_each_entry(f, &en->values) {
2907 sb_addf(buf, " %d,", f->value);
2908 }
2909 sb_adds(buf,
2910 "\n"
2911 "};\n");
2912
2913 t = mp_iopc_enum_build_ranges(t_pool(), en);
2914 range = iopc_put_range(buf, &t);
2915
2916 sb_addf(buf,
2917 "static const lstr_t %s__names[] = {\n",
2918 tbase);
2919 tab_for_each_entry(value, &en->values) {
2920 sb_addf(buf, " LSTR_IMMED(\"%s\"),\n", value->name);
2921 }
2922 sb_adds(buf, "};\n");
2923 tab_for_each_entry(attr, &en->attrs) {
2924 if (attr->desc->id == IOPC_ATTR_STRICT) {
2925 SET_BIT(&flags, IOP_ENUM_STRICT);
2926 break;
2927 }
2928 }
2929
2930 for (int i = 0; i < en->values.len; i++) {
2931 t_scope;
2932 iopc_enum_field_t *f = en->values.tab[i];
2933
2934 tab_for_each_entry(attr, &f->attrs) {
2935 if (attr->desc->id == IOPC_ATTR_ALIAS) {
2936 SET_BIT(&flags, IOP_ENUM_ALIASES);
2937 tab_for_each_entry(alias, &attr->args) {
2938 if (!alias_count) {
2939 sb_addf(buf, "static const iop_enum_aliases_t "
2940 "%s__aliases = {\n", tbase);
2941 sb_adds(buf, " .aliases = {\n");
2942 }
2943 sb_addf(buf, " { "
2944 ".pos = %d, .name = LSTR_IMMED(\"%*pM\") },\n",
2945 i, LSTR_FMT_ARG(alias.v.s));
2946 alias_count++;
2947 }
2948 }
2949 }
2950 }
2951 if (alias_count > 0) {
2952 sb_adds(buf, " },\n");
2953 sb_addf(buf, " .len = %d\n", alias_count);
2954 sb_adds(buf, "};\n");
2955 }
2956
2957 tab_for_each_entry(val, &en->values) {
2958 t_scope;
2959 lstr_t fname;
2960 const char *var_pfx;
2961 int nb_enum_value_attrs;
2962 unsigned enum_value_attrs_flags;
2963
2964 fname = t_lstr_ascii_tolower(LSTR(val->name));
2965 var_pfx = t_fmt("%s__%*pM", tbase, LSTR_FMT_ARG(fname));
2966
2967 iopc_dump_attr_table(&iopc_attr_kind_enum_value_g, &val->comments,
2968 &val->attrs, var_pfx, buf,
2969 &enum_value_attrs_flags, &nb_enum_value_attrs);
2970 if (nb_enum_value_attrs) {
2971 values_have_attributes = true;
2972 }
2973 iopc_dump_attrs_ref(&values_attrs_body, enum_value_attrs_flags,
2974 nb_enum_value_attrs, var_pfx, true,
2975 iopc_attr_kind_enum_value_g.ext);
2976 }
2977
2978 if (values_have_attributes) {
2979 iopc_dump_attrs_ref_body(&iopc_attr_kind_enum_value_g, tbase,
2980 LSTR_SB_V(&values_attrs_body), true, buf);
2981 }
2982
2983 iopc_dump_attrs(&iopc_attr_kind_enum_g, &en->comments, &en->attrs,
2984 tbase, buf, &has_attrs);
2985 if (has_attrs || values_have_attributes) {
2986 SET_BIT(&flags, IOP_ENUM_EXTENDED);
2987 }
2988
2989 sb_addf(buf,
2990 "iop_enum_t const %s__e = {\n"
2991 " .name = LSTR_IMMED(\"%s\"),\n"
2992 " .fullname = LSTR_IMMED(\"%s.%s\"),\n"
2993 " .names = %s__names,\n"
2994 " .values = %s__values,\n"
2995 " .ranges = iop__ranges__%d,\n"
2996 " .ranges_len = countof(iop__ranges__%d) / 2,\n"
2997 " .enum_len = %d,\n",
2998 tbase, en->name, iopc_path_dot(pkg->name), en->name,
2999 tbase, tbase, range, range, en->values.len);
3000 if (flags) {
3001 sb_addf(buf, " .flags = %u,\n", flags);
3002 }
3003 if (has_attrs) {
3004 sb_addf(buf, " .en_attrs = &%s__e_desc_attrs,\n", tbase);
3005 }
3006 if (values_have_attributes) {
3007 sb_addf(buf, " .values_attrs = %s__e_desc_values_attrs,\n", tbase);
3008 }
3009 if (alias_count > 0) {
3010 sb_addf(buf, " .aliases = &%s__aliases,\n", tbase);
3011 }
3012 sb_addf(buf,
3013 "};\n"
3014 "iop_enum_t const * const %s__ep = &%s__e;\n"
3015 "\n"
3016 "/* }""}} */\n", tbase, tbase);
3017}

3020/* {{{ Constraint checks. */
3021
3022static bool iopc_has_constraints(const qv_t(iopc_attr) *attrs)
3023{
3024 tab_for_each_entry(attr, attrs) {
3025 if ((attr->desc->flags & IOPC_ATTR_F_CONSTRAINT)) {
3026 return true;
3027 }
3028 }
3029 return false;
3030}
3031
3032static bool iopc_is_private(const qv_t(iopc_attr) *attrs)
3033{
3034 tab_for_each_entry(attr, attrs) {
3035 if (attr->desc->id == IOPC_ATTR_PRIVATE) {
3036 return true;
3037 }
3038 }
3039 return false;
3040}
3041
3042static void iopc_struct_check_constraints(iopc_struct_t *st)
3043{
3044 if (st->checked_constraints)
3045 return;
3046 st->checked_constraints = true;
3047
3048 if (iopc_has_constraints(&st->attrs))
3049 st->has_constraints = true;
3050
3051 tab_for_each_entry(f, &st->fields) {
3052 if (iopc_has_constraints(&f->attrs))
3053 st->has_constraints = true;
3054
3055 switch (f->kind) {
3056 case IOP_T_STRUCT:
3057 case IOP_T_UNION:
3058 iopc_struct_check_constraints(f->struct_def);
3059 if (f->struct_def->has_constraints) {
3060 st->has_constraints = true;
3061 }
3062 break;
3063
3064 case IOP_T_ENUM:
3065 if (iopc_has_constraints(&f->enum_def->attrs)) {
3066 st->has_constraints = true;
3067 }
3068 break;
3069
3070 default:
3071 break;
3072 }
3073 }
3074}

3082 default:
3083 case STRUCT_TYPE_STRUCT: return "Structure";
3084 case STRUCT_TYPE_CLASS: return "Class";
3085 case STRUCT_TYPE_UNION: return "Union";
3086 }
3087}

3089static int iopc_put_struct_fields(sb_t *buf, const iopc_struct_t *st,
3090 const char *tbase, bool has_attrs,
3091 const char *as_base)
3092{
3093 if (iopc_is_class(st->type) || iopc_is_snmp_st(st->type)
3094 || st->contains_snmp_info)
3095 {
3096 t_scope;
3097 lstr_t st_attrs = t_lstr_fmt("&%s__s_desc_attrs", tbase);
3098 lstr_t fields_attrs = t_lstr_fmt("%s__desc_fields_attrs", as_base);
3099
3100 sb_addf(buf,
3101 " .flags = %d,\n"
3102 " .is_union = %s,\n"
3103 " .st_attrs = %s,\n"
3104 " .fields_attrs = %s,\n",
3105 st->flags, st->type == STRUCT_TYPE_UNION ? "true": "false",
3106 has_attrs ? st_attrs.s : "NULL",
3107 st->has_fields_attrs ? fields_attrs.s : "NULL");
3108
3109 sb_adds(buf, LVL1 "{\n");
3110 if (iopc_is_class(st->type)) {
3111 sb_addf(buf, LVL2 ".class_attrs = &%s__class_s,\n", tbase);
3112 } else {
3113 sb_addf(buf, LVL2".snmp_attrs = &%s__snmp_attrs__s,\n", tbase);
3114 }
3115 sb_adds(buf, LVL1 "}\n");
3116 return 0;
3117 }
3118
3119 if (iopc_is_snmp_st(st->type)) {
3120 throw_loc("snmp can only be used with iopc v4", st->loc);
3121 }
3122 if (st->flags) {
3123 sb_addf(buf, LVL1 ".flags = %d,\n", st->flags);
3124 }
3125 if (st->type == STRUCT_TYPE_UNION) {
3126 sb_adds(buf, LVL1 ".is_union = true,\n");
3127 }
3128 if (has_attrs) {
3129 sb_addf(buf, LVL1 ".st_attrs = &%s__s_desc_attrs,\n", tbase);
3130 }
3131 if (st->has_fields_attrs) {
3132 sb_addf(buf, LVL1 ".fields_attrs = %s__desc_fields_attrs,\n",
3133 as_base);
3134 }
3135 if (st->type == STRUCT_TYPE_CLASS) {
3136 sb_addf(buf, LVL1 ".class_attrs = &%s__class_s,\n", tbase);
3137 }
3138 return 0;
3139}
3140
3141#undef LVL1
3142#undef LVL2
3143#undef LVL3
3144#undef LVL4
3145
3146/** Build the range used to associate an IOP tag to a struct field. */
3147static iop_array_i32_t mp_iopc_struct_build_ranges(mem_pool_t *mp,
3148 const iopc_struct_t *st)
3149{
3150 qv_t(i32) t;
3151 int last_tag = INT_MIN;
3152
3153 assert(st->fields_by_tag.len == st->fields.len);
3154 mp_qv_init(mp, &t, 2 * st->fields_by_tag.len + 1);
3155 tab_enumerate(i, f, &st->fields_by_tag) {
3156 if (++last_tag != f->tag) {
3157 qv_append(&t, i);
3158 qv_append(&t, f->tag);
3159 last_tag = f->tag;
3160 }
3161 }
3162 qv_append(&t, st->fields_by_tag.len);
3163 mp_realloc_from(mp, &t.tab, t.size, t.len);
3164
3165 return IOP_TYPED_ARRAY_TAB(i32, &t);
3166}

3168static void
3169write_class_attrs(sb_t *buf, const iopc_struct_t *st, const char *tbase,
3170 const char *as_base)
3171{
3172 assert (iopc_is_class(st->type));
3173 sb_addf(buf,
3174 "static %siop_class_attrs_t %s__class_s = {\n",
3175 CONST, tbase);
3176 if (st->extends.len) {
3177 t_scope;
3178
3179 sb_addf(buf, " .parent = &%s__%s__s,\n",
3180 t_iopc_path_to_c(st->extends.tab[0]->pkg->name),
3181 t_iopc_name_to_c(st->extends.tab[0]->st->name));
3182 }
3183 if (st->nb_real_static_fields) {
3184 sb_addf(buf,
3185 " .static_fields = %s__static_fields,\n"
3186 " .static_fields_len = %d,\n",
3187 as_base, st->nb_real_static_fields);
3188 }
3189 if (st->is_abstract) {
3190 sb_adds(buf, " .is_abstract = true,\n");
3191 }
3192 if (iopc_is_private(&st->attrs)) {
3193 sb_adds(buf, " .is_private = true,\n");
3194 }
3195 sb_addf(buf,
3196 " .class_id = %d,\n", st->class_id);
3197 sb_adds(buf, "};\n");
3198}
3199
3200__must_check__ static int
3201write_struct(sb_t *buf, const iopc_struct_t *st, const iopc_pkg_t *pkg,
3202 const char *tbase, const char *real_tbase,
3203 const char *sname, const char *as_base,
3204 int rpc_oid, int range, bool has_attrs)
3205{
3206 if (iopc_is_class(st->type)) {
3207 write_class_attrs(buf, st, tbase, as_base);
3208 } else
3209 if (iopc_is_snmp_st(st->type)) {
3210 iopc_extends_t *xt = st->extends.tab[0];
3211
3212 iopc_dump_snmp_attrs(buf, xt->st, xt->pkg, tbase, st->oid,
3213 xt->is_snmp_root, false, false,
3214 IOP_T_STRUCT);
3215 }
3216 if (st->contains_snmp_info) {
3217 iopc_dump_snmp_attrs(buf, st, pkg, tbase, rpc_oid, false,
3218 true, false, IOP_T_STRUCT);
3219 }
3220 sb_addf(buf,
3221 "const iop_struct_t %s__s = {\n"
3222 " .fullname = LSTR_IMMED(\"%s.%s\"),\n"
3223 " .fields = %s__desc_fields,\n"
3224 " .ranges = iop__ranges__%d,\n"
3225 " .ranges_len = countof(iop__ranges__%d) / 2,\n"
3226 " .fields_len = countof(%s__desc_fields),\n",
3227 tbase, iopc_path_dot(pkg->name),
3228 sname, as_base, range, range, as_base);
3229
3230 if (!iopc_is_snmp_obj(st->type)) {
3231 sb_addf(buf, " .size = sizeof(%s__t),\n", real_tbase);
3232 }
3233 RETHROW(iopc_put_struct_fields(buf, st, real_tbase, has_attrs, as_base));
3234 sb_adds(buf, "};\n");
3235 sb_addf(buf, "iop_struct_t const * const %s__sp = &%s__s;\n",
3236 tbase, tbase);
3237
3238 return 0;
3239}
3240
3241static int
3242iopc_struct_dump_src(sb_t *buf, const iopc_pkg_t *pkg,
3243 const char *pkg_name,
3244 iopc_struct_t *st, const qv_t(lstr) *paliases,
3245 const char *iface_name, int rpc_oid)
3246{
3247 t_scope;
3248 const char *comment = get_struct_type_desc(st->type);
3249 const char *tname = t_iopc_name_to_c(st->name);
3250 const char *iname = st->iface ? st->iface->name : NULL;
3251 char *tbase = iname ? t_fmt("%s__%s__%s", pkg_name,
3252 t_iopc_name_to_c(iname), tname)
3253 : t_fmt("%s__%s", pkg_name, tname);
3254 char *sname = iname ? t_fmt("%s.%s", iname, st->name)
3255 : t_fmt("%s", st->name);
3256 char *as_base;
3257 int range;
3258 iop_array_i32_t t;
3259 bool has_attrs;
3260
3261 sb_addf(buf, "/* %s %s.%s {""{{ */\n\n",
3262 comment, iopc_path_dot(pkg->name), sname);
3263
3264 if (st->same_as) {
3265 iopc_struct_t *as = st->same_as;
3266
3267 if (as->iface) {
3268 sb_addf(buf, "/* same as %s.%s.%s */\n\n",
3269 iopc_path_dot(pkg->name), as->iface->name, as->name);
3270 as_base = t_fmt("%s__%s__%s", pkg_name,
3271 t_iopc_name_to_c(as->iface->name),
3272 t_iopc_name_to_c(as->name));
3273 } else {
3274 sb_addf(buf, "/* same as %s.%s */\n\n",
3275 iopc_path_dot(pkg->name), as->name);
3276 as_base = t_fmt("%s__%s", pkg_name,
3277 t_iopc_name_to_c(as->name));
3278 }
3279 /* all the attributes and constraints work has already been done with
3280 * the as struct, so re-use it */
3281 st->flags = as->flags;
3282 st->has_fields_attrs = as->has_fields_attrs;
3283 st->has_constraints = as->has_constraints;
3284 } else {
3285 qv_t(iopc_attrs) fields_attrs;
3286
3287 as_base = tbase;
3288
3289 qv_init(&fields_attrs);
3290
3291 /* generate <tbase>__<field>__snmp_attrs__s for fields of snmpIface
3292 * rpcs */
3293 if (st->contains_snmp_info) {
3294 char *fbase;
3295 iopc_extends_t *xt;
3296
3297 assert(st->fields_by_tag.len == st->fields.len);
3298 tab_for_each_entry(field, &st->fields_by_tag) {
3299 fbase = t_fmt("%s__%s", tbase,
3300 t_iopc_name_to_c(field->name));
3301 xt = field->parents.tab[0];
3302
3303 iopc_dump_snmp_attrs(buf, xt->st, xt->pkg, fbase,
3304 field->field_origin->tag,
3305 xt->is_snmp_root,
3306 false, false, field->field_origin->kind);
3307 }
3308 } else
3309 if (iopc_is_snmp_st(st->type)) {
3310 char *fbase;
3311
3312 assert(st->fields_by_tag.len == st->fields.len);
3313 tab_for_each_entry(field, &st->fields_by_tag) {
3314 fbase = t_fmt("%s__%s", tbase,
3315 t_iopc_name_to_c(field->name));
3316
3317 iopc_dump_snmp_attrs(buf, st, pkg, fbase, field->tag,
3318 false, false, false, field->kind);
3319 }
3320 }
3321
3322 /* check attributes and generate everything that is needed for
3323 * <tbase>__desc_fields_attrs (attributes, constraints func and help)
3324 */
3325 assert(st->fields_by_tag.len == st->fields.len);
3326 tab_for_each_entry(field, &st->fields_by_tag) {
3327 iopc_attrs_t attrs;
3328
3329 iopc_attrs_init(&attrs);
3330
3331 RETHROW(iopc_dump_field_attrs(buf, st, tbase, field, &attrs));
3332 if (attrs.checkf_name.len || attrs.flags) {
3333 st->has_fields_attrs = true;
3334 }
3335 qv_append(&fields_attrs, attrs);
3336 }
3337
3338 /* generate <tbase>__desc_fields_attrs */
3339 if (st->has_fields_attrs) {
3340 SET_BIT(&st->flags, IOP_STRUCT_EXTENDED);
3341 sb_addf(buf,
3342 "static iop_field_attrs_t const %s__desc_fields_attrs[] = {\n",
3343 tbase);
3344 assert(st->fields_by_tag.len == st->fields.len);
3345 tab_enumerate(i, f, &st->fields_by_tag) {
3346 iopc_dump_field_attrs_src(buf, st, tbase, f,
3347 &fields_attrs.tab[i]);
3348 }
3349 sb_adds(buf, "};\n");
3350 }
3351
3352 /* generate <tbase>__desc_fields */
3353 sb_addf(buf, "static iop_field_t %s%s__desc_fields[] = {\n", CONST,
3354 tbase);
3355 assert(st->fields_by_tag.len == st->fields.len);
3356 tab_enumerate(i, f, &st->fields_by_tag) {
3357 iopc_dump_field_src(buf, st, tbase, f, &fields_attrs.tab[i]);
3358 }
3359 sb_adds(buf,
3360 "};\n");
3361
3362 qv_deep_wipe(&fields_attrs, iopc_attrs_wipe);
3363
3364 iopc_struct_check_constraints(st);
3365 if (st->has_constraints) {
3366 SET_BIT(&st->flags, IOP_STRUCT_HAS_CONSTRAINTS);
3367 }
3368
3369 /* generate static fields */
3370 if (st->nb_real_static_fields) {
3371 iopc_struct_dump_static_fields_src(buf, st, tbase);
3372 }
3373
3374 if (iopc_is_class(st->type)) {
3375 SET_BIT(&st->flags, IOP_STRUCT_EXTENDED);
3376 SET_BIT(&st->flags, IOP_STRUCT_IS_CLASS);
3377 SET_BIT(&st->flags, IOP_STRUCT_STATIC_HAS_TYPE);
3378 } else
3379 if (iopc_is_snmp_obj(st->type)) {
3380 SET_BIT(&st->flags, IOP_STRUCT_EXTENDED);
3381 SET_BIT(&st->flags, IOP_STRUCT_IS_SNMP_OBJ);
3382
3383 /* check @snmpParam attribute */
3384 tab_for_each_entry(attr, &st->attrs) {
3385 if (attr->desc->id == IOPC_ATTR_SNMP_PARAM) {
3386 SET_BIT(&st->flags, IOP_STRUCT_IS_SNMP_PARAM);
3387 break;
3388 }
3389 }
3390 } else
3391 if (iopc_is_snmp_tbl(st->type)) {
3392 SET_BIT(&st->flags, IOP_STRUCT_EXTENDED);
3393 SET_BIT(&st->flags, IOP_STRUCT_IS_SNMP_TBL);
3394 }
3395 }
3396
3397 t = mp_iopc_struct_build_ranges(t_pool(), st);
3398 range = iopc_put_range(buf, &t);
3399
3400 iopc_dump_attrs(&iopc_attr_kind_struct_g, &st->comments, &st->attrs,
3401 tbase, buf, &has_attrs);
3402 if (has_attrs) {
3403 SET_BIT(&st->flags, IOP_STRUCT_EXTENDED);
3404 }
3405
3406 RETHROW(write_struct(buf, st, pkg, tbase, tbase, sname, as_base, rpc_oid,
3407 range, has_attrs));
3408
3409 if (paliases) {
3410 tab_for_each_entry(alias, paliases) {
3411 t_scope;
3412 const char *alias_tname;
3413 const char *alias_tbase;
3414 const char *alias_sname;
3415
3416 alias_tname = t_iopc_name_to_c(alias.s);
3417 alias_tbase = iname ? t_fmt("%s__%s__%s", pkg_name,
3418 t_iopc_name_to_c(iname),
3419 alias_tname)
3420 : t_fmt("%s__%s", pkg_name, alias_tname);
3421 alias_sname = iname ? t_fmt("%s.%s", iname, alias.s) : alias.s;
3422 RETHROW(write_struct(buf, st, pkg, alias_tbase, tbase,
3423 alias_sname, as_base, rpc_oid, range,
3424 has_attrs));
3425 }
3426 }
3427
3428 sb_adds(buf, "\n/* }""}} */\n");
3429
3430 return 0;
3431}

3436static void
3437iopc_dump_rpc_defines(sb_t *buf, const char *ibase, const iopc_field_t *field,
3438 const char *alias_name)
3439{
3440 t_scope;
3441 const char *name = alias_name ? alias_name : field->name;
3442 const char *tbase_arg;
3443 const char *tbase_ref;
3444
3445 tbase_arg = t_fmt("%s__%s", ibase, t_iopc_name_to_c(name));
3446 tbase_ref = t_fmt("%s__%s", t_iopc_path_to_c(field->type_path),
3447 t_iopc_name_to_c(field->type_name));

3454 tbase_arg, tbase_ref);
3455 }
3456 sb_addf(buf, "#define %s__s %s__s\n", tbase_arg,
3457 tbase_ref);
3458}
