3519
3520static void
3521iopc_register_fun(sb_t *buf, const char *ibase, const iopc_fun_t *f,
3522 const char *falias_name)
3523{
3524 sb_addf(buf,
3525 " {\n"
3526 " .name = LSTR_IMMED(\"%s\"),\n"
3527 " .tag = %d,\n",
3528 falias_name ?: f->name, f->tag);
3529
3530 iopc_register_fun_struct(buf, ibase, &f->arg, falias_name, "args",
3531 "args ");
3532 iopc_register_fun_struct(buf, ibase, &f->res, falias_name, "res",
3533 "result");
3534 iopc_register_fun_struct(buf, ibase, &f->exn, falias_name, "exn",
3535 "exn ");
3536
3537 if (f->fun_is_async) {
3538 sb_addf(buf,
3539 " .async = true,\n");
3540 }
3541
3542 /* handle flags */
3543 {
3544 unsigned flags = 0;
3545
3546 if (falias_name) {
3547 SET_BIT(&flags, IOP_RPC_IS_ALIAS);
3548 } else
3549 if (iopc_fun_has_alias(f)) {
3550 SET_BIT(&flags, IOP_RPC_HAS_ALIAS);
3551 }
3552 if (flags) {
3553 sb_addf(buf, " .flags = %u,\n", flags);
3554 }
3555 }
3556 sb_adds(buf, " },\n");
3557}
3558
3559static inline void
3560iopc_iface_dump_rpc_attrs(sb_t *buf, const char *ibase, iopc_iface_t *iface)
3561{
3562 unsigned n_func_and_alias = 0;
3563 qv_t(iopc_attrs) rpc_attrs;
3564 bool dump_attrs = false;
3565
3566 qv_init(&rpc_attrs);
3567 tab_for_each_entry(f, &iface->funs) {
3568 iopc_attrs_t attrs;
3569
3570 n_func_and_alias++;
3571 iopc_attrs_init(&attrs);
3572 iopc_dump_rpc_attrs(buf, ibase, f, &attrs, &n_func_and_alias);
3573 if (attrs.attrs_len)
3574 dump_attrs = true;
3575 qv_append(&rpc_attrs, attrs);
3576 }
3577
3578 if (dump_attrs) {
3579 const iopc_attr_kind_t *attr_kind = &iopc_attr_kind_rpc_g;
3580
3581 SET_BIT(&iface->flags, IOP_IFACE_EXTENDED);
3582 sb_addf(buf,
3583 "static %s const %s__%s[] = {\n",
3584 attr_kind->attrs_typename, ibase, attr_kind->attrs_var_sfx);
3585 tab_enumerate(pos, f, &iface->funs) {
3586 t_scope;
3587 iopc_attrs_t attrs = rpc_attrs.tab[pos];
3588 int aliases_count = 0;
3589
3590 iopc_dump_rpc_attrs_src(buf, &attrs);
3591
3592 /* dump attributes for aliases
3593 * these attributes are the same as for *f but IOPC_ATTR_ALIAS */
3594 tab_for_each_entry(attr, &f->attrs) {
3595 if (attr->desc->id == IOPC_ATTR_ALIAS) {
3596 aliases_count = attr->args.len;
3597 break;
3598 }
3599 }
3600 attrs.attrs_len -= aliases_count;
3601 CLR_BIT(&attrs.flags, IOP_RPC_ALIAS);
3602 assert (!attrs.attrs_len || attrs.flags);
3603 attrs.attrs_name = t_lstr_fmt("%*pM_na",
3604 LSTR_FMT_ARG(attrs.attrs_name));
3605 while (aliases_count--) {
3606 iopc_dump_rpc_attrs_src(buf, &attrs);
3607 }
3608 }
3609 sb_adds(buf, "};\n");
3610 }
3611 qv_deep_wipe(&rpc_attrs, iopc_attrs_wipe);
3612}

3614static int
3615iopc_iface_struct_dump_src(sb_t *buf, const iopc_pkg_t *pkg,
3616 const char *pkg_name, const char *ibase,
3617 const iopc_fun_t *fun,
3618 const iopc_fun_struct_t *fun_st, const char *type)
3619{
3620 t_scope;
3621 qv_t(lstr) aliases;
3622
3623 if (iopc_fun_struct_is_void(fun_st)) {
3624 return 0;
3625 }
3626 t_qv_init(&aliases, 0);
3627 t_iopc_get_aliases(fun, type, &aliases);
3628
3629 if (fun_st->is_anonymous) {
3630 RETHROW(iopc_struct_dump_src(buf, pkg, pkg_name,
3631 fun_st->anonymous_struct, &aliases, NULL,
3632 0));
3633 } else {
3634 /* When the function argument is just a reference to another
3635 * structure, we just yield several #define. */
3636 iopc_dump_rpc_defines(buf, ibase, fun_st->existing_struct, NULL);
3637 tab_for_each_entry(alias, &aliases) {
3638 iopc_dump_rpc_defines(buf, ibase, fun_st->existing_struct,
3639 alias.s);
3640 }
3641 }
3642
3643 return 0;
3644}

3646static int
3647iopc_iface_dump_src(sb_t *buf, const iopc_pkg_t *pkg,
3648 const char *pkg_name, iopc_iface_t *iface)
3649{
3650 t_scope;
3651 const char *iname = t_iopc_name_to_c(iface->name);
3652 char *ibase = t_fmt("%s__%s", pkg_name, iname);
3653 qv_t(lstr) aliases;
3654 bool has_attrs;
3655
3656 t_qv_init(&aliases, 16);
3657 sb_addf(buf, "/* Interface %s.%s {""{{ */\n",
3658 iopc_path_dot(pkg->name), iface->name);
3659
3660 if (iface->type == IFACE_TYPE_SNMP_IFACE) {
3661 SET_BIT(&iface->flags, IOP_IFACE_IS_SNMP_IFACE);
3662
3663 tab_for_each_entry(fun, &iface->funs) {
3664 if (!iopc_fun_struct_is_void(&fun->arg)) {
3665 /* snmpIface can only have "args" and anonymous funs */
3666 t_iopc_get_aliases(fun, "Args", &aliases);
3667 if (fun->arg.is_anonymous) {
3668 RETHROW(iopc_struct_dump_src(
3669 buf, pkg, pkg_name, fun->arg.anonymous_struct,
3670 &aliases, t_iopc_name_to_c(iface->name),
3671 fun->tag));
3672 } else {
3673 throw_loc("should not happen", fun->loc);
3674 }
3675 }
3676 }
3677 } else {
3678 tab_for_each_entry(fun, &iface->funs) {
3679 iopc_iface_struct_dump_src(buf, pkg, pkg_name, ibase, fun,
3680 &fun->arg, "Args");
3681 iopc_iface_struct_dump_src(buf, pkg, pkg_name, ibase, fun,
3682 &fun->res, "Res");
3683 iopc_iface_struct_dump_src(buf, pkg, pkg_name, ibase, fun,
3684 &fun->exn, "Exn");
3685 }
3686 }
3687
3688 sb_addf(buf, "static iop_rpc_t %s%s__if_funs[] = {\n", CONST, ibase);
3689 tab_for_each_entry(f, &iface->funs) {
3690 iopc_register_fun(buf, ibase, f, NULL);
3691 t_iopc_get_aliases(f, "", &aliases);
3692 tab_for_each_entry(alias, &aliases) {
3693 iopc_register_fun(buf, ibase, f, alias.s);
3694 }
3695 }
3696 sb_adds(buf, "};\n");
3697
3698 if (iface->type == IFACE_TYPE_SNMP_IFACE) {
3699 iopc_extends_t *xt = iface->extends.tab[0];
3700
3701 iopc_dump_snmp_attrs(buf, xt->st, xt->pkg, ibase, iface->oid, false,
3702 false, true, IOP_T_STRUCT);
3703 }
3704
3705 iopc_iface_dump_rpc_attrs(buf, ibase, iface);
3706
3707 iopc_dump_attrs(&iopc_attr_kind_iface_g, &iface->comments, &iface->attrs,
3708 ibase, buf, &has_attrs);
3709 if (has_attrs) {
3710 SET_BIT(&iface->flags, IOP_IFACE_HAS_ATTRS);
3711 }
3712
3713 sb_addf(buf,
3714 "const iop_iface_t %s__if = {\n"
3715 " .fullname = LSTR_IMMED(\"%s.%s\"),\n"
3716 " .funs = %s__if_funs,\n"
3717 " .funs_len = countof(%s__if_funs),\n",
3718 ibase, iopc_path_dot(pkg->name),
3719 iface->name, ibase, ibase);
3720 if (iface->flags) {
3721 sb_addf(buf, " .flags = %d,\n", iface->flags);
3722 }
3723 if (TST_BIT(&iface->flags, IOP_IFACE_EXTENDED)) {
3724 sb_addf(buf, " .rpc_attrs = %s__rpc_desc_attrs,\n", ibase);
3725 }
3726 if (TST_BIT(&iface->flags, IOP_IFACE_HAS_ATTRS)) {
3727 sb_addf(buf, " .iface_attrs = &%s__desc_if_attrs,\n", ibase);
3728 }
3729 if (TST_BIT(&iface->flags, IOP_IFACE_IS_SNMP_IFACE)) {
3730 sb_addf(buf, " .snmp_iface_attrs = &%s__snmp_attrs__s,\n", ibase);
3731 }
3732 sb_adds(buf, "};\n");
3733 sb_addf(buf, "const iop_iface_t * const %s__ifp = &%s__if;\n\n",
3734 ibase, ibase);
3735 sb_adds(buf, "/* }""}} */\n");
3736
3737 return 0;
3738}

3914#define RO_WARN \
3915 "/***** THIS FILE IS AUTOGENERATED DO NOT MODIFY DIRECTLY ! *****/\n"
3916
3917static bool strendswith(const char *s, const char *needle, const char **endp)
3918{
3919 size_t nlen = strlen(needle);
3920 size_t slen = strlen(s);
3921
3922 if (nlen > slen)
3923 return false;
3924 if (endp)
3925 *endp = s + slen - nlen;
3926 return strequal(s + slen - nlen, needle);
3927}
3928
3929static size_t path_count_atoms(const char *s)
3930{
3931 size_t n = 0;
3932
3933 if (*s == 0) {
3934 return 0;
3935 }
3936 if (*s == '/') {
3937 s++;
3938 }
3939 while ((s = strchr(s, '/'))) {
3940 n++;
3941 s++;
3942 }
3943 return n + 1;
3944}
3945
3946static size_t common_prefix(const char *s, const char *t)
3947{
3948 size_t n = 0;
3949
3950 while (s[n] && s[n] == t[n])
3951 n++;
3952 return n;
3953}
3954
3955static int put_include(sb_t *sb, const char *ext,
3956 iopc_pkg_t *pkg, const iopc_pkg_t *us)
3957{
3958 const char *iop_path = iopc_path_slash(pkg->name);
3959
3960 sb_adds(sb, "#include \"");
3961 if (_G.resolve_includes) {
3962 char our_path[PATH_MAX], dep_path[PATH_MAX];
3963 int pfx, n;
3964 char *p;
3965
3966 path_dirname(dep_path, sizeof(dep_path), us->file);
3967 path_canonify(our_path, sizeof(our_path), dep_path);
3968 path_canonify(dep_path, sizeof(dep_path), pkg->file);
3969 if (!strendswith(dep_path, iop_path, (const char **)&p))
3970 goto no_rel;
3971 assert (p > dep_path && p[-1] == '/');
3972 --p;
3973 dep_path[p - dep_path] = '\0';
3974 pfx = common_prefix(our_path, dep_path);
3975 while (pfx > 0 && our_path[pfx - 1] != '/')
3976 pfx--;
3977 if (pfx == 1)
3978 goto no_rel;
3979 n = path_count_atoms(our_path + pfx);
3980 for (int j = 0; j < n; j++) {
3981 sb_adds(sb, "../");
3982 }
3983 if (dep_path[pfx] == '/')
3984 pfx++;
3985 if (dep_path[pfx])
3986 sb_addf(sb, "%s/", dep_path + pfx);
3987 }
3988 sb_addf(sb, "%*pM%s\"\n", (int)strlen(iop_path) - 4, iop_path, ext);
3989 return 0;
3990
3991 no_rel:
3992 throw_error("[%s] unable to make a relative #include path for %s",
3993 iopc_path_slash(pkg->name), iop_path);
3994}
3995
3996int iopc_do_c(iopc_pkg_t *pkg, const char *outdir)
3997{
3998 t_scope;
3999 SB_8k(buf);
4000 qv_t(iopc_pkg) t_deps, t_weak_deps, i_deps;
4001 const char *pkg_name;
4002 char path[PATH_MAX];
4003 int res = 0;
4004
4005#define IOPC_DO_C_RETHROW(e) \
4006 do { \
4007 if ((res = (e)) < 0) { \
4008 goto end; \
4009 } \
4010 } while (0)
4011
4012 /*----- prepare stuff -----*/
4013 qv_inita(&t_deps, 1024);
4014 qv_inita(&t_weak_deps, 1024);
4015 qv_inita(&i_deps, 1024);
4016
4017 pkg_name = t_iopc_path_to_c(pkg->name);
4018 iopc_pkg_get_deps(pkg, IOPC_PKG_GET_DEPS_INCLUDE_ALL,
4019 &t_deps, &t_weak_deps, &i_deps);
4020
4021 iopc_set_path(outdir, pkg, "-tdef.iop.h", sizeof(path), path,
4022 !!iopc_do_c_g.iop_compat_header);
4023
4024 /*----- dump the typedef header ------*/
4025 sb_sets(&buf, RO_WARN);
4026 sb_addf(&buf,
4027 "#ifndef IOP_HEADER_GUARD_%s_TYPEDEFS_H\n"
4028 "#define IOP_HEADER_GUARD_%s_TYPEDEFS_H\n"
4029 "\n", pkg_name, pkg_name);
4030 if (iopc_do_c_g.iop_compat_header) {
4031 sb_adds(&buf, iopc_do_c_g.iop_compat_header);
4032 sb_addc(&buf, '\n');
4033 } else {
4034 sb_adds(&buf,
4035 "#include <lib-common/core.h>\n"
4036 "#include <lib-common/iop/internals.h>\n"
4037 "\n");
4038 }
4039
4040 tab_for_each_entry(en, &pkg->enums) {
4041 iopc_enum_dump_tdef_hdr(&buf, pkg_name, en);
4042 }
4043 tab_for_each_entry(st, &pkg->structs) {
4044 iopc_struct_dump_tdef_hdr(&buf, pkg_name, st, NULL);
4045
4046 if (iopc_is_snmp_st(st->type)) {
4047 sb_addf(&buf,
4048 "/*----- snmp fields of struct %s.%s -----*/\n",
4049 iopc_path_dot(pkg->name), st->name);
4050 tab_for_each_entry(f, &st->fields) {
4051 iopc_snmp_field_dump_tdef_hdr(&buf, pkg_name, st, f);
4052 }
4053 }
4054 }
4055 sb_adds(&buf, "#endif\n");
4056
4057 IOPC_DO_C_RETHROW(iopc_write_file(&buf, path));
4058
4059 /*----- dump the types header -----*/
4060 sb_sets(&buf, RO_WARN);
4061 sb_addf(&buf,
4062 "#ifndef IOP_HEADER_GUARD_%s_TYPES_H\n"
4063 "#define IOP_HEADER_GUARD_%s_TYPES_H\n"
4064 "\n"
4065 "#include \"%s-tdef.iop.h\"\n"
4066 "\n", pkg_name, pkg_name, iopc_path_basename(pkg->name));
4067
4068 tab_for_each_entry(dep, &t_weak_deps) {
4069 IOPC_DO_C_RETHROW(put_include(&buf, "-tdef.iop.h", dep, pkg));
4070 }
4071 tab_for_each_entry(dep, &t_deps) {
4072 IOPC_DO_C_RETHROW(put_include(&buf, "-t.iop.h", dep, pkg));
4073 }
4074 if (t_deps.len || t_weak_deps.len) {
4075 sb_adds(&buf, "\n");
4076 }
4077
4078 sb_adds(&buf,
4079 "#if __has_feature(nullability)\n"
4080 "#pragma GCC diagnostic push\n"
4081 "#pragma GCC diagnostic error \"-Wnullability-completeness\"\n"
4082 "#endif\n\n");
4083
4084 tab_for_each_entry(en, &pkg->enums) {
4085 iopc_enum_dump_hdr(&buf, pkg_name, en);
4086 }
4087 tab_for_each_entry(st, &pkg->structs) {
4088 if (st->type == STRUCT_TYPE_UNION) {
4089 iopc_union_dump_hdr(&buf, pkg_name, st);
4090 } else {
4091 iopc_struct_dump_hdr(&buf, pkg, pkg_name, st, NULL);
4092 }
4093
4094 if (iopc_is_snmp_st(st->type)) {
4095 tab_for_each_entry(field, &st->fields) {
4096 iopc_snmp_field_dump_hdr(&buf, pkg_name, st, field);
4097 }
4098 }
4099 }
4100
4101 sb_adds(&buf,
4102 "#if __has_feature(nullability)\n"
4103 "#pragma GCC diagnostic pop\n"
4104 "#endif\n\n");
4105
4106 sb_adds(&buf, "#endif\n");
4107
4108 strcpy(path + strlen(path) - strlen("-tdef.iop.h"), "-t.iop.h");
4109 IOPC_DO_C_RETHROW(iopc_write_file(&buf, path));
4110
4111 /*----- dump the iface header -----*/
4112 sb_sets(&buf, RO_WARN);
4113 sb_addf(&buf,
4114 "#ifndef IOP_HEADER_GUARD_%s_H\n"
4115 "#define IOP_HEADER_GUARD_%s_H\n"
4116 "\n"
4117 "#include \"%s-t.iop.h\"\n",
4118 pkg_name, pkg_name, iopc_path_basename(pkg->name));
4119 tab_for_each_entry(dep, &t_deps) {
4120 IOPC_DO_C_RETHROW(put_include(&buf, ".iop.h", dep, pkg));
4121 }
4122 tab_for_each_entry(dep, &i_deps) {
4123 IOPC_DO_C_RETHROW(put_include(&buf, ".iop.h", dep, pkg));
4124 }
4125 sb_adds(&buf, "\n");
4126 tab_for_each_entry(iface, &pkg->ifaces) {
4127 qv_sort(iopc_fun)(&iface->funs,
4128 ^int (iopc_fun_t * const *f1,
4129 iopc_fun_t * const *f2) {
4130 return (*f1)->tag - (*f2)->tag;
4131 });
4132 iopc_iface_dump_tdef_hdr(&buf, pkg_name, iface);
4133 }
4134 sb_adds(&buf, "\n");
4135 tab_for_each_entry(iface, &pkg->ifaces) {
4136 iopc_iface_dump_hdr(&buf, pkg, pkg_name, iface);
4137 }
4138 tab_for_each_entry(mod, &pkg->modules) {
4139 iopc_module_dump_hdr(&buf, pkg, pkg_name, mod);
4140 }
4141 iopc_pkg_dump_hdr(&buf, pkg, pkg_name);
4142 sb_adds(&buf, "#endif\n");
4143
4144 strcpy(path + strlen(path) - strlen("-t.iop.h"), ".iop.h");
4145 IOPC_DO_C_RETHROW(iopc_write_file(&buf, path));
4146
4147 /*----- dump the C file -----*/
4148 sb_sets(&buf, RO_WARN);
4149 sb_addf(&buf,
4150 "#ifndef linux\n"
4151 "# warning \"%s assumed linux alignments\"\n"
4152 "#endif\n", iopc_path_slash(pkg->name));
4153#ifdef __x86_64__
4154 sb_addf(&buf,
4155 "#ifndef __x86_64__\n"
4156 "# warning \"%s assumed x86_64 alignments\"\n"
4157 "#endif\n", iopc_path_slash(pkg->name));
4158#endif
4159#ifdef __i386__
4160 sb_addf(&buf,
4161 "#ifndef __i386__\n"
4162 "# warning \"%s assumed i386 alignments\"\n"
4163 "#endif\n", iopc_path_slash(pkg->name));
4164#endif
4165 sb_addf(&buf,
4166 "\n"
4167 "#include \"%s.iop.h\"\n",
4168 iopc_path_basename(pkg->name));
4169 tab_for_each_entry(dep, &t_weak_deps) {
4170 IOPC_DO_C_RETHROW(put_include(&buf, ".iop.h", dep, pkg));
4171 }
4172 sb_adds(&buf, "\n");
4173 tab_for_each_entry(en, &pkg->enums) {
4174 iopc_enum_dump_src(&buf, pkg, pkg_name, en);
4175 }
4176 tab_for_each_entry(st, &pkg->structs) {
4177 IOPC_DO_C_RETHROW(iopc_struct_dump_src(&buf, pkg, pkg_name, st,
4178 NULL, NULL, 0));
4179 }
4180 tab_for_each_entry(iface, &pkg->ifaces) {
4181 IOPC_DO_C_RETHROW(iopc_iface_dump_src(&buf, pkg, pkg_name, iface));
4182 }
4183 tab_for_each_entry(mod, &pkg->modules) {
4184 iopc_module_dump_src(&buf, pkg, pkg_name, mod);
4185 }
4186 iopc_pkg_dump_src(&buf, pkg, pkg_name, &t_deps, &i_deps);
4187 sb_addc(&buf, '\n');
4188
4189 path[strlen(path) - 1] = 'c';
4190 IOPC_DO_C_RETHROW(iopc_write_file(&buf, path));
4191
4192#undef IOPC_DO_C_RETHROW
4193
4194 /*----- collect memory -----*/
4195 end:
4196 qv_wipe(&t_deps);
4197 qv_wipe(&t_weak_deps);
4198 qv_wipe(&i_deps);
4199 iopc_put_range_cleanup();
4200 return res;
4201}

4214/* {{{ IOP struct/union */
4215
4216static int mp_iopc_field_to_desc(mem_pool_t *mp, const iopc_field_t *f,
4217 const iopc_struct_t *st, uint16_t *offset,
4218 iop_field_t *fdesc, sb_t *err)
4219{
4220 uint16_t size;
4221
4222 if (f->repeat == IOP_R_DEFVAL) {
4223 sb_sets(err, "default values are not supported yet");
4224 return -1;
4225 }
4226
4227 *offset = ROUND_UP(*offset, f->align);
4228
4229 /* The "size" is not the same between iop_field_t and iopc_field_t:
4230 *
4231 * iopc_field_t: size of the field (as returned by fieldtypeof)
4232 * iop_field_t: size of the underlying type except for class
4233 */
4234 if (iop_type_is_scalar(f->kind)) {
4235 if (f->repeat == IOP_R_OPTIONAL) {
4236 iop_opt_type_get_size_and_alignment(f->kind, &size, NULL);
4237 } else {
4238 iop_scalar_type_get_size_and_alignment(f->kind, &size, NULL);
4239 }
4240 } else {
4241 if (iopc_field_type_is_class(f)) {
4242 size = sizeof(void *);
4243 } else
4244 if (f->has_external_type) {
4245 size = f->external_st->size;
4246 } else {
4247 size = f->struct_def->size;
4248 }
4249 }
4250
4251 *fdesc = (iop_field_t){
4252 .name = mp_lstr_dups(mp, f->name, -1),
4253 .tag = f->tag,
4254 .tag_len = iopc_tag_len(f->tag),
4255 .repeat = f->repeat,
4256 .type = f->kind,
4257 .data_offs = *offset,
4258 .flags = iopc_field_build_flags(f, st, NULL), /* TODO attrs */
4259 /* TODO default value */
4260 .size = size,
4261 };
4262
4263 if (!iop_type_is_scalar(fdesc->type)) {
4264 if (f->has_external_type) {
4265 fdesc->u1.st_desc = f->external_st;
4266 } else {
4267 /* TODO We're going to have to load dependancies first if we want
4268 * that to work in multi-package contexts. */
4269 fdesc->u1.st_desc = f->struct_def->desc;
4270 }
4271
4272 assert (fdesc->u1.st_desc);
4273 } else
4274 if (fdesc->type == IOP_T_ENUM) {
4275 if (f->has_external_type) {
4276 fdesc->u1.en_desc = f->external_en;
4277 } else {
4278 /* TODO Ditto. */
4279 fdesc->u1.en_desc = f->enum_def->desc;
4280 }
4281
4282 assert (fdesc->u1.en_desc);
4283 }
4284
4285 if (st->type != STRUCT_TYPE_UNION) {
4286 *offset += f->size;
4287 }
4288
4289 return 0;
4290}
4291
4292static iop_struct_t *
4293mp_iopc_struct_to_desc(mem_pool_t *mp, iopc_struct_t *st,
4294 const iopc_pkg_t *pkg, sb_t *err)
4295{
4296 iop_struct_t *st_desc;
4297 iop_field_t *fields;
4298 uint16_t offset = 0;
4299 iop_array_i32_t ranges;
4300
4301 if (st->type == STRUCT_TYPE_UNION) {
4302 offset = sizeof(uint16_t);
4303 }
4304
4305 assert(st->fields_by_tag.len == st->fields.len);
4306 fields = mp_new_raw(mp, iop_field_t, st->fields_in_c_struct_order.len);
4307 tab_for_each_entry(f, &st->fields_in_c_struct_order) {
4308 if (mp_iopc_field_to_desc(mp, f, st, &offset, &fields[f->field_pos],
4309 err) < 0)
4310 {
4311 sb_prependf(err, "field `%s': ", f->name);
4312 return NULL;
4313 }
4314 }
4315
4316 if (st->type == STRUCT_TYPE_UNION) {
4317 /* The anonymous union field offset depends on its alignment, which
4318 * depends of the IOP union field with the biggest alignment. This
4319 * loop realigns all the fields offsets on the biggest offset.
4320 */
4321 tab_for_each_pos(pos, &st->fields_in_c_struct_order) {
4322 fields[pos].data_offs = offset;
4323 }
4324 }
4325
4326 ranges = mp_iopc_struct_build_ranges(mp, st);
4327
4328 {
4329 iop_struct_t _st_desc = {
4330 .fullname = mp_build_fullname(mp, pkg, st->name),
4331 .fields = fields,
4332 .fields_len = st->fields_in_c_struct_order.len,
4333 .ranges = ranges.tab,
4334 .ranges_len = ranges.len / 2,
4335 .size = st->size, /* TODO Check correctness */
4336 .flags = st->flags,
4337 .is_union = (st->type == STRUCT_TYPE_UNION),
4338 /* TODO st_attrs */
4339 /* TODO field_attrs */
4340 /* TODO class_attrs */
4341 };
4342
4343 st_desc = mp_new_raw(mp, iop_struct_t, 1);
4344 /* XXX Work-around all the const fields in 'iop_struct_t'. */
4345 p_copy(st_desc, &_st_desc, 1);
4346 st->desc = st_desc;
4347 };
4348
4349 return st_desc;
4350}

4354
4355static iop_enum_t *mp_iopc_enum_to_desc(mem_pool_t *mp,
4356 iopc_enum_t *en,
4357 const iopc_pkg_t *pkg)
4358{
4359 iop_enum_t *en_desc;
4360 iop_array_i32_t ranges;
4361 lstr_t *names;
4362 int32_t *values;
4363 int pos = 0;
4364
4365 ranges = mp_iopc_enum_build_ranges(mp, en);
4366 names = mp_new_raw(mp, lstr_t, en->values.len);
4367 values = mp_new_raw(mp, int32_t, en->values.len);
4368 tab_for_each_entry(f, &en->values) {
4369 names[pos] = mp_lstr_dups(mp, f->name, -1);
4370 values[pos] = f->value;
4371 pos++;
4372 }
4373
4374 {
4375 iop_enum_t _en_desc = {
4376 .name = mp_lstr_dup(mp, LSTR(en->name)),
4377 .fullname = mp_build_fullname(mp, pkg, en->name),
4378 .names = names,
4379 .values = values,
4380 .ranges = ranges.tab,
4381 .ranges_len = ranges.len / 2,
4382 .enum_len = en->values.len,
4383 /* TODO attrs */
4384 /* TODO aliases */
4385 };
4386
4387 en_desc = mp_new_raw(mp, iop_enum_t, 1);
4388 p_copy(en_desc, &_en_desc, 1);
4389 en->desc = en_desc;
4390 }
4391
4392 return en_desc;
4393}

4396/* {{{ IOP package */
4397
4398iop_pkg_t *mp_iopc_pkg_to_desc(mem_pool_t *mp, iopc_pkg_t *pkg, sb_t *err)
4399{
4400 iop_pkg_t *pkg_desc;
4401 const iop_struct_t **structs;
4402 const iop_struct_t **wst;
4403 const iop_enum_t **enums;
4404 const iop_enum_t **wen;
4405
4406 tab_for_each_entry(st, &pkg->structs) {
4407 iopc_struct_optimize(st);
4408 }
4409
4410 enums = mp_new_raw(mp, const iop_enum_t *, pkg->enums.len + 1);
4411 wen = enums;
4412 tab_for_each_entry(en, &pkg->enums) {
4413 *wen++ = mp_iopc_enum_to_desc(mp, en, pkg);
4414 }
4415 *wen = NULL;
4416
4417 structs = mp_new_raw(mp, const iop_struct_t *, pkg->structs.len + 1);
4418 wst = structs;
4419 tab_for_each_entry(st, &pkg->structs) {
4420 *wst = mp_iopc_struct_to_desc(mp, st, pkg, err);
4421 if (!*wst) {
4422 sb_prependf(err, "struct %s: ", st->name);
4423 return NULL;
4424 }
4425
4426 wst++;
4427 }
4428 *wst = NULL;
4429
4430 {
4431 iop_pkg_t _pkg_desc = {
4432 .name = mp_lstr_dups(mp, iopc_path_dot(pkg->name), -1),
4433 .enums = enums,
4434 .structs = structs,
4435 /* TODO (later) ifaces, mods */
4436 /* TODO deps */
4437 };
4438
4439 pkg_desc = mp_new_raw(mp, iop_pkg_t, 1);
4440 /* XXX Work-around all the const fields in 'iop_pkg_t'. */
4441 p_copy(pkg_desc, &_pkg_desc, 1);
4442 }
4443
4444 return pkg_desc;
4445}
